	('3b6e426e-18d8-4ac7-8dee-b828afc58e1c', 'Local Specialty Home Barista (Shropshire & Borders)', 'Enthusiast home barista within easy delivery distance of the Shropshire hills who buys whole bean coffee regularly, dials in espresso at home, and values organic sourcing plus the story of an off-grid, renewably powered roastery. Motivated by freshness, ethical credentials, and consistent results in the cup.', 'Consumer (Home Coffee / Specialty Food & Beverage)', 'Individual / Household (1–4 people)', 'United Kingdom — Shropshire (incl. Shrewsbury, Oswestry, Ludlow, Bridgnorth) and nearby borders', '{"Inconsistent roast dates and freshness from online marketplaces; beans arrive too old to dial in well","Wasting 100–250g dialing in a new coffee and not knowing the right recipe (dose/yield/time)","Uncertainty about which beans suit milk drinks vs straight espresso or filter","Subscription anxiety: fear of being locked in, forgetting to cancel, or receiving too much coffee","Concern about greenwashing; wants verifiable organic credentials and ethical sourcing"}', '{"Get consistently fresh whole beans delivered on a predictable schedule (every 2–4 weeks) to avoid stale supermarket coffee","Improve espresso consistency by matching roast level to their grinder and machine (reduce sour/under-extracted shots)","Support an organic, renewably powered off-grid roastery with a strong provenance story","Discover a dependable ''house coffee'' they can dial in quickly without wasting beans","Have an easy way to pause, swap, or change grind/bean type as their routine changes"}', 'GBP £25–£45 per month on coffee subscriptions (typical 1–2 bags/month, plus occasional extras)', '{"Primary grocery buyer","Home barista enthusiast","Household finance decision-maker"}', '{"Facebook & Instagram","Meta Shops / in-app checkout (where available)","Shopify/WooCommerce subscription checkout familiarity","Apple Pay / Google Pay","WhatsApp Messenger for quick questions","Home espresso setup (e.g., Sage/Breville, Gaggia, Rancilio, Lelit) with a burr grinder"}', '{"Keeping espresso dialed in as beans age and humidity changes in the UK","Choosing between single origin and blend without tasting notes being too vague","Managing delivery timing so they never run out mid-week","Balancing ethical purchasing with price sensitivity"}', '{"Meta ads featuring off-grid roastery story + organic proof points aimed at Shropshire postcodes","Subscription offer with flexible controls: pause/skip/swap roasts, plus ''espresso dial-in'' brew guide","Retargeting video viewers with a ''fresh roast date guarantee'' message","Local social proof creatives: reviews, awards, and Shropshire hills origin angle","Upsell: sample packs, seasonal releases, and recommended espresso recipes by grinder/machine type"}', '2025-12-28 18:21:32.916+00', '2025-12-28 18:21:32.916+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3aa3975b-cf18-4768-a6f2-d72abfc812f4'),
	('dab1ecd1-db96-45f7-a845-236b09b4978f', 'Tech & Startup Leaders in NYC Prioritizing Comfort + Style', 'Founders, product leaders, and senior tech professionals who dress smart-casual daily and want comfortable, premium jeans that fit perfectly for meetings, events, and travel—ordered online with minimal hassle.', 'Technology (Startups, SaaS, FinTech)', '10–500 employees', 'United States — New York, NY (Brooklyn/SoHo/Flatiron)', '{"Jeans that fit in the morning feel restrictive by afternoon (especially at the waist/hips)","Off-the-rack rises and inseams don’t match body proportions, causing bunching or pulling","Too many denim options; hard to find a reliable ''daily driver'' pair","Online buying uncertainty: fear of returns, delays, and inconsistent quality","Needs versatile washes (dark indigo/black) without excessive fading or distressing"}', '{"Get a consistent fit that works with sneakers, boots, and smart-casual layers","Find jeans that are comfortable for long seated days and commuting","Upgrade wardrobe to look polished for investor meetings, demos, and conferences","Minimize time spent shopping by using saved measurements and reordering","Choose fabric and stretch level that stays sharp and doesn’t bag out at the knees"}', 'USD $220–$400 per pair; USD $600–$1,200 per year across 2–4 pairs', '{"Individual buyer (Founder/CTO/VP Product)","Executive assistant or partner influencing gift purchases/wardrobe refresh"}', '{"iPhone or Android",Instagram,Facebook,"Google Pay","Apple Pay","Shop Pay","Calendly (for optional fitting appointments)"}', '{"Wants confidence in fabric quality, stretch recovery, and durability before buying","Needs clear guidance on fit preferences (taper, rise, leg opening) without jargon","Busy schedule makes returning items inconvenient","Preference for brands with strong reviews and transparent policies"}', '{"Create a ''Find Your Fit'' quiz that recommends rise/taper based on body type and style","Run Instagram Reels ads demonstrating before/after fit on common body types","Offer bundle pricing for 2–3 pairs with different washes using the same measurements","Use lookalike audiences based on purchasers in NYC and retarget site visitors with fit-guarantee messaging"}', '2025-12-29 17:09:23.402+00', '2025-12-29 19:59:21.52332+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3aa3975b-cf18-4768-a6f2-d72abfc812f4'),
	('c6bc90f8-8d50-4366-93d6-793f534fc3d4', 'Sammy Name', 'Parents and families often travel; this ICP targets short-term rental hosts and small property managers who want memorable, themed amenities that boost reviews. They need guest-friendly, visually cohesive bathroom items that signal cleanliness and care.', 'Hospitality (Short-Term Rentals / Property Management)', '1–20 employees (or solo host with multiple properties)', 'United States (high STR density: Florida, California, Texas, Tennessee, Colorado, Arizona)', '{"Generic bulk soaps feel cheap and don’t differentiate the listing; guests perceive lower value","Frequent restocking: soaps run out, get wet/messy, or are left unusable between turnovers","Guest sensitivity concerns (fragrance/allergies) can trigger complaints and refunds","Inconsistent amenities across properties leads to uneven guest experiences and review risk","Hard to find items that are both durable in humid bathrooms and aesthetically cohesive for photos"}', '{"Upgrade guest bathrooms with a distinctive amenity (lemon soap) that feels premium and photo-worthy","Increase 5-star reviews by signaling cleanliness and thoughtful details upon check-in","Standardize bathroom amenity kits across properties to reduce replenishment time","Create a brandable theme (fresh, bright lemon) that guests remember and mention in reviews","Control costs while preventing theft/waste through right-sized products and packaging"}', '$200–$2,000/month depending on property count and occupancy; $3–$8 per turnover per bathroom for soap/amenities', '{Host/Owner,"Property Manager","Operations/Turnover Coordinator"}', '{Airbnb/VRBO,"Property management system (Hostaway, Guesty, Lodgify, or OwnerRez)","Automations (Turno for cleaning scheduling)","Inventory/reorder tracking (Google Sheets, Airtable)","Canva (for guest book/amenity signage)"}', '{"Choosing a scent profile that feels ‘fresh’ without being overpowering for sensitive guests","Packaging that withstands storage and humid bathrooms without degrading","Aligning amenity styling with listing photos to improve conversion on Airbnb/VRBO","Managing cost creep when occupancy spikes during peak seasons"}', '{"Create ‘Lemon Fresh Welcome’ bathroom kits (soap + lemon-themed accessory) for each turnover","Add a small bathroom sign: ‘Enjoy our Lemon Drops soap’ to prompt mentions in reviews","Upsell add-on: optional purchase link for guests who want to buy the soap after their stay","Seasonal refresh: spring/summer lemon theme for listing photo updates and higher click-through","Bulk reorder program with predictable cadence tied to occupancy forecasts"}', '2025-12-15 20:53:26.376+00', '2025-12-29 17:54:11.460987+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, '#EDEDED', '#9D4EDD', NULL, 'female/25-34/female_25-34_003.png', NULL, '498645dd-41d3-4e20-9f0c-291e130dafe3'),
	('a1759bf6-7aa1-473a-a28a-733748754f46', 'Health-First Young Family Shopper', 'Parents with 1–2 children who buy weekly groceries online/in-store and want an organic, low-additive apple juice they feel good about serving at home. They respond to Facebook offers, family-focused creative, and clear proof points (organic, B-Corp).', 'Consumer (Households / Grocery shoppers)', 'N/A (Household)', 'United Kingdom (England, Scotland, Wales, Northern Ireland)', '{"Confusion over labels: ''from concentrate'' vs not, added sugar claims, and unclear ingredient lists","Concern about giving kids overly sweet drinks and wanting simpler ingredients","Hard to find a genuinely ethical/values-led juice brand that is also affordable for regular home use","Skepticism about greenwashing; wants proof that B-Corp and organic claims are legitimate","Inconsistent availability of preferred juice brands in local supermarkets"}', '{"Find an organic apple juice for home consumption that feels safe and trustworthy for children","Reduce exposure to artificial additives, colours, and preservatives in family drinks","Keep the fridge stocked with a convenient, kid-friendly drink option for lunchboxes and after school","Choose brands that align with values (ethical sourcing, B-Corp) without sacrificing taste","Stay within a realistic weekly grocery/drinks spend while still buying organic"}', '£12–£25 per month for apple juice and family juice drinks', '{"Primary grocery shopper (often parent/guardian)","Co-parent/partner who approves repeat purchases"}', '{"Facebook and Facebook Groups","Instagram (secondary)","Online grocery platforms (Tesco, Sainsbury’s, Asda, Ocado)","Mobile payment (Apple Pay/Google Pay)","Subscription/auto-repeat purchases (where available)"}', '{"Balancing organic preferences with price sensitivity during weekly grocery planning","Managing kids’ taste preferences while avoiding sugary drinks","Finding brands that deliver consistent quality and availability month to month"}', '{"Facebook campaigns featuring lunchbox/after-school moments and ''organic + B-Corp'' trust cues","Family bundle pricing (multi-pack) and subscribe-and-save for regular home consumption","Clear ingredient/processing explanation ads (e.g., no artificial additives, how it’s made)","Retargeting grocery shoppers who engage with ethical/organic content and family food pages"}', '2026-01-08 21:07:04.177+00', '2026-01-08 21:07:04.177+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('ca02d89f-ce13-4f9a-aae1-fc76285b74c0', 'Overtired First-Time Parent in Urban California', 'First-time mom or dad with a newborn/infant who is overwhelmed by sleep deprivation and actively searching Facebook for simple, reliable ways to get longer stretches of sleep using soothing audio routines (white noise + lullabies + stories).', 'Consumer (Parents & Families)', 'N/A (Individual household)', 'United States — California (San Francisco Bay Area, Los Angeles, San Diego)', '{"Baby startles awake from apartment/neighbor noise and sudden household sounds","Parent anxiety that they are ''doing it wrong'' due to conflicting sleep advice online","Spending money on multiple sleep aids that don’t stick because routines aren’t consistent","Nighttime soothing takes 45–90 minutes, leaving no time to recover between wake-ups","Baby only sleeps when held, making transfers to the crib/bassinet fail repeatedly"}', '{"Help a 0–6 month baby fall asleep faster (within 15–20 minutes) after feeding","Reduce nighttime wake-ups from 4–6 times to 1–3 times per night","Create a consistent bedtime routine combining calming white noise and a short story","Avoid relying on rocking/feeding-to-sleep every time to prevent parent burnout","Improve parent sleep to function at work and during daytime caregiving"}', 'USD $30–$120 total for a story + sound solution; willing to spend up to USD $15–$30/month for add-ons if it demonstrably improves sleep within 7–14 days', '{"Mother (primary nighttime caregiver)","Father/partner (co-decision maker)","Occasionally: pediatrician advice influences purchase"}', '{"iPhone or Android smartphone","Facebook app (Groups, Marketplace, Ads)","Bluetooth speaker or nursery sound machine","Spotify/Apple Music (optional for audio routines)","Baby tracking app (e.g., Huckleberry-type sleep tracking)"}', '{"Maintaining a routine when baby schedules change weekly","Distinguishing normal newborn waking from preventable waking due to noise","Keeping volume/time settings safe and consistent across nights","Coordinating with partner shifts and differing soothing styles"}', '{"Position the family story package as a plug-and-play bedtime script (same steps nightly)","Offer short ''3-minute bedtime reset'' audio for overtired nights","Retarget Facebook engagers with testimonials about faster crib transfers","Bundle calm white noise + lullaby + story playlists by baby age (0–3, 4–6 months)"}', '2026-01-09 14:55:26.703+00', '2026-01-09 15:10:32.137169+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, '#FFD93D', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'a72f7a2b-71f4-469c-b8fc-4ab4a2c3420a'),
	('16bbfa79-b1d8-4f3a-9c85-10c519b7b16b', 'Upgrade-Seeking Home Espresso Owner (Giftable Subscription Buyer)', 'A UK household in Shropshire where someone has recently bought (or been gifted) an espresso machine and wants an easy, impressive subscription that makes their coffee taste better quickly. Often buys as a gift for a partner/parent and values convenience, guidance, and a premium feel.', 'Consumer (Gifting / Home Coffee)', 'Individual / Household (1–6 people)', 'United Kingdom — Shropshire', '{"New espresso owners get bitter/sour shots and assume the machine is faulty","Doesn’t know what roast level to choose for latte/cappuccino vs straight espresso","Gift subscriptions feel risky if they can’t control delivery dates or add a gift note","Overchoice: too many origins/processing methods without simple recommendations","Worries the recipient won’t like ''experimental'' flavours; wants crowd-pleasing options"}', '{"Find a ''no-stress'' coffee subscription that reliably tastes better than supermarket beans","Give a memorable gift with a strong story (organic + off-grid renewable roastery in the Shropshire hills)","Receive clear brew guidance for espresso and milk drinks to avoid early frustration","Choose the right frequency/size so the recipient doesn’t run out or get overwhelmed","Feel confident the brand is reputable (awards/reviews) and ethically aligned"}', 'GBP £30–£60 per month (or GBP £90–£180 upfront for a 3-month gift subscription)', '{"Gift buyer (partner/relative/friend)","Household purchaser","Recipient (influencer on taste preferences)"}', '{"Facebook & Instagram (Reels/Stories)","Meta click-to-message (Messenger/WhatsApp)","Klarna/Clearpay awareness (if offered) for gifting","Email inbox for delivery updates","Beginner espresso gear (e.g., Sage Bambino/Barista Express) and entry-level grinder"}', '{"Reducing early churn by quickly getting the customer to a good-tasting cup","Communicating flavour expectations simply (chocolate/nutty vs fruity) without jargon","Coordinating gifting dates and first delivery timing","Overcoming the perception that subscriptions are inflexible"}', '{"Meta campaigns targeting ''recent espresso machine buyers'' interests in Shropshire + gifting occasions (Christmas, birthdays, Father’s Day)","Landing page with 3 simple picks: ''Milk Drinks'', ''Espresso'', ''Filter'' and a guided quiz","Add-on: printed brew card + QR code to a dial-in video tailored for common Sage machines","Gift subscription creatives featuring the off-grid roastery and award proof to increase trust","Post-purchase onboarding sequence: grind size tips, recipe baseline, and how to pause/skip"}', '2025-12-28 18:21:33.063+00', '2025-12-28 18:21:33.063+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '3aa3975b-cf18-4768-a6f2-d72abfc812f4'),
	('efcd8fa2-71c9-4199-a360-31a35be5182e', 'Test this', 'A parent influencer (primarily moms) building a small DTC shop or curated storefront for their audience. Relies on TikTok for reach and Pinterest for evergreen traffic; wants a signature ‘cute but practical’ product that fits family routines and home aesthetics.', 'Creator Commerce / DTC Retail', '1–3 employees (creator + VA + fulfillment partner)', 'United States, Canada, United Kingdom, Australia (English-speaking creator markets)', '{"Audience fatigue: followers don’t want another generic soap; needs a story/visual hook (lemon theme) to stand out","Unpredictable sales spikes after viral videos causing stockouts and missed revenue","Negative comments if product appears overly fragranced, harsh, or not family-friendly","Limited time to manage customer service, shipping questions, and returns as a solo operator","Ad spend waste when creative doesn’t quickly communicate the product benefit in the first 2 seconds"}', '{"Launch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and shareLaunch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and share Launch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and share Launch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and share","Drive sales with short-form demos (unboxing, bathroom reset, sink-side styling) that highlight Lemon Soap’s look and lather","Offer affordable ‘treat yourself’ items under $20 that convert from impulse clicks","Increase repeat purchase rate with multi-pack refills and limited drops tied to content series","Build a consistent brand aesthetic that fits bright, clean, cheerful kitchen/bathroom content"}', '$1,000–$8,000/month for inventory + $500–$5,000/month for TikTok Spark Ads and creator production', '{Creator/Founder,"Talent Manager (sometimes)",Operations/VA,"3PL Account Manager (if outsourced)"}', '{Shopify,"TikTok Shop (optional) + TikTok Business","Pinterest Business","Klaviyo or Mailchimp",Canva/CapCut,"Link-in-bio tool (Linktree/Beacons)","3PL (ShipBob/ShipMonk) or in-home shipping tools"}', '{"Turning views into purchases with clear CTAs and frictionless checkout","Keeping product claims compliant (skin sensitivity, ingredients, fragrance)","Coordinating limited drops, pre-orders, and shipping timelines without hurting trust","Maintaining brand consistency across TikTok, Pinterest, and the storefront"}', '{"UGC-first ad angles: ‘Bathroom reset with me’, ‘guest bathroom upgrade’, ‘clean girl citrus vibe’","Pinterest SEO strategy: pins linking to bundles (lemon soap + accessories) and ‘bathroom refresh’ checklists","Limited-run ‘Lemon Drops’ seasonal scents/labels to create collectability and repeat orders","Creator collabs: duet/stitch campaigns showing sink-side styling and lather shots","Launch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and shareLaunch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and shareLaunch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and shareLaunch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and shareLaunch or expand a creator shop with a signature lemon-themed product that audiences immediately understand and share","Here''s another line"}', '2025-12-15 20:53:26.208+00', '2025-12-18 17:09:42.128308+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, '#EDEDED', '#9D4EDD', NULL, 'female/25-34/female_25-34_001.png', NULL, NULL),
	('2ab3e7c4-633b-4923-b2a9-0c07ee06dd80', 'Ethical & Organic Lifestyle Subscriber (Low-Fuss Filter/AeroPress)', 'A Shropshire-based UK customer prioritising organic food choices and low-carbon, local(ish) sourcing. Enjoys quality coffee at home using AeroPress, V60, Chemex, or cafetière and wants a dependable organic subscription that aligns with their values, with minimal tinkering and clear tasting notes.', 'Consumer (Organic / Ethical Lifestyle)', 'Individual / Household (1–5 people)', 'United Kingdom — Shropshire', '{"Organic options often taste flat or generic compared to specialty coffee","Confusion about grind size and brew ratios for different filter devices","Skepticism about sustainability claims without specifics (energy use, packaging, sourcing)","Doesn’t want overly acidic or ''funky'' coffees that feel unpredictable","Delivery frequency mismatches lead to either running out or accumulating too much coffee"}', '{"Buy organic coffee that fits an ethically minded household routine without extra effort","Support renewable energy and low-impact production via an off-grid roastery story","Receive consistent, easy-to-brew coffees for filter methods (AeroPress/V60/cafetière)","Maintain a stable monthly coffee spend and avoid last-minute grocery runs","Feel good about transparency: roast date, origin, organic certification, and packaging choices"}', 'GBP £18–£35 per month (typically 1 bag/month for filter, occasional second bag)', '{"Household grocery buyer","Sustainability/values-driven purchaser","Partner/spouse (shared household spend approval)"}', '{"Facebook Groups (local Shropshire communities, organic living, home brewing groups)","Instagram feed for brand story and product education","Subscription checkout (Shopify/WooCommerce familiarity)","Email newsletters for delivery reminders and brew guides","Brew gear: AeroPress, V60, Chemex, cafetière; basic burr grinder or pre-ground preference"}', '{"Balancing approachability with specialty credentials so the coffee feels ''safe'' to buy repeatedly","Educating without overwhelming: simple brew recipes that work first time","Proving organic + sustainability benefits in a way that is credible and not preachy","Minimising churn by matching roast profiles to filter preferences"}', '{"Value-led Meta creatives: organic + off-grid renewable power + Shropshire hills provenance","Subscription tier for ''Smooth Organic Filter'' with predictable flavour profile and simple brew recipe","Content that answers practical questions: grind size charts, 2-minute AeroPress recipe, cafetière tips","Retargeting people engaging with sustainability content to a low-commitment starter subscription","Upsell: compostable/low-impact packaging option (if available) and seasonal organic single origins"}', '2025-12-28 18:21:33.131+00', '2025-12-28 18:57:49.558403+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, '#9D4EDD', NULL, NULL, NULL, '3aa3975b-cf18-4768-a6f2-d72abfc812f4'),
	('fae6da61-5d56-4bde-99e5-f79217ec033b', 'Health-First Busy Parent (After-School Treat Buyer)', 'Parents of primary-school children who buy snacks and treats weekly and want a fun option they feel good about. They are influenced by short-form videos, school-gate chat, and what their kids ask for after seeing it on TikTok/Instagram.', 'Consumer (Households / Parenting & Family)', 'N/A (Household)', 'United Kingdom (England—Greater London, Manchester, Birmingham and surrounding suburbs)', '{"Feels most ice lollies are too artificial, too sugary, or have ingredients they can’t pronounce","Child rejects ‘healthy’ snacks unless they look fun and feel like a treat","Limited time to compare brands; needs quick trust signals (ingredients, reviews, clear claims)","Worries about waste if kids don’t like the flavour (needs confidence strawberry will land)","Struggles to find treats that work for school holidays, park days, and home without mess"}', '{"Find an after-school treat that feels healthier than typical ice lollies (prefers all-natural ingredients)","Keep a small stock of freezer-friendly treats for playdates, weekends, and last-minute rewards","Avoid ingredient worry (wants simple, recognisable ingredients and clear flavour expectations like strawberry)","Choose products that reduce parent guilt while still exciting kids with bright, fun packaging","Discover new kid-approved snacks via Instagram Reels/TikTok that are easy to buy again"}', 'GBP £10–£25 per month for ice pops (typically 1–3 multipacks, depending on promotions and season)', '{"Parent/Guardian (primary grocery buyer)","Co-parent/Partner (secondary approver)","Child (influencer/ultimate preference)"}', '{Instagram,TikTok,"WhatsApp parent groups","Grocery delivery apps (e.g., Tesco, Sainsbury’s, Asda, Ocado)","Apple Pay/Google Pay"}', '{"Balancing healthier choices with kids’ taste and ‘cool factor’ expectations","Managing frequent snack requests in warmer months without overspending","Building trust in a newer brand quickly (especially for ingredients and taste)"}', '{"Run TikTok/IG creatives featuring quick ingredient callouts + kid taste reactions to strawberry","Offer multipack and ‘family freezer stock-up’ bundles with straightforward pricing","Seasonal parent hooks: half-term, summer holidays, after-school routine content","UGC campaigns encouraging parents to show ‘approved by my kid’ moments"}', '2026-01-24 14:43:57.04+00', '2026-01-24 14:43:57.04+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'fafe78e2-eb02-45f0-8666-3701bb5976f6'),
	('d8b68c3a-3a26-433f-bf95-4d5dd21620e2', 'K‑Pop & Trend Culture Teen (Social-First Treat Buyer)', 'Teens who are highly active on TikTok/Instagram, follow K-pop trends, and look for fun, aesthetic snacks they can show in videos or share with friends. They gravitate to standout packaging and reliable flavours like strawberry.', 'Consumer (Teen/Student Lifestyle)', 'N/A (Individual/Household)', 'United Kingdom (UK-wide; strongest in major cities and commuter towns)', '{"Bored of standard ice pops that feel generic and not ‘post-worthy’","Limited discretionary money; won’t repurchase if price feels high for the experience","Needs easy availability—if it’s hard to find again, hype fades quickly","Taste risk: dislikes overly artificial strawberry flavours and chemical aftertaste","Peer influence: doesn’t want to bring something that friends think is ‘basic’"}', '{"Buy a treat that looks cool on camera (packaging aesthetics matter as much as taste)","Try ‘trend’ snacks that feel unique compared to standard supermarket ice lollies","Share/bring something fun for hangouts, sleepovers, and after-school meetups","Find a reliable go-to flavour (strawberry) that won’t disappoint","Stay within personal spending limits while still buying something that feels premium"}', 'GBP £5–£20 per month from pocket money/part-time earnings (often 1–4 impulse buys depending on availability)', '{"Teen (primary chooser and purchaser when available)","Parent/Guardian (sometimes pays/approves household shopping)"}', '{TikTok,Instagram,Snapchat,Spotify,"Mobile payments (Apple Pay/Google Pay)","Food delivery/snack delivery apps (where available)"}', '{"Maintaining novelty—trends move fast and attention is short","Converting a one-time ‘aesthetic’ purchase into repeat buying","Ensuring product is easy to find locally after discovery on social"}', '{"Creator-led TikTok content: unbox + first bite + packaging ASMR with strawberry focus","Limited-edition K‑pop-inspired packaging drops to drive urgency and collecting","Friend-share multipacks or ‘2 for’ offers positioned for hangouts","Hashtag challenges that feature the product visually (colour, packaging, bite shots)"}', '2026-01-24 14:43:57.04+00', '2026-01-24 14:43:57.04+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'fafe78e2-eb02-45f0-8666-3701bb5976f6'),
	('878794cb-bf00-450e-8e4a-a81b072f9af4', 'Boutique Parent Gift-Shop Owner (E-commerce + Local Pickup)', 'Owner-operator parent running a curated online gift shop (often with a small studio or local pickup). Stocks playful, aesthetic, scent-forward items for self-care, kids’ bathrooms, and small gifts; prioritizes photogenic products that perform on Pinterest and TikTok.', 'E-commerce Retail (Gifts, Bath & Body, Home Decor)', '1–5 employees', 'United States (suburban/metro areas with strong gift-buying demand)', '{"Struggles to find novelty soaps that are actually giftable (cute but not cheap-looking) and won’t melt/warp in shipping","Low conversion on “bath basics” because products look generic in product photos and don’t stand out in social feeds","Returns/complaints from fragrance expectations (too strong, too weak, not “fresh lemon”) affecting reviews","Needs packaging that feels premium and gift-ready without increasing fulfillment time","Inventory risk: buying too deep into a scent/theme that doesn’t sell after the initial social spike"}', '{"Add a low-risk, high-margin hero product that can be sold as a $12–$24 giftable add-on (lemon soap) with strong impulse appeal","Increase average order value via curated bundles (soap + lemon-themed bathroom accessory + small curiosity item)","Create seasonal drops that convert around spring cleaning, Mother’s Day, teacher gifts, Easter baskets, and summer hosting","Source products that photograph well and can be reliably restocked for repeat customers","Reduce customer acquisition costs by leaning into Pinterest search intent (bathroom refresh, lemon decor, gift ideas)"}', '$500–$2,500/month for inventory testing + $300–$1,500/month for content/ads (Pinterest/TikTok)', '{Owner/Founder,"Buyer/Merchandiser (often the owner)","Operations/Fulfillment Lead (part-time or contractor)"}', '{Shopify,Klaviyo,"Pinterest Business + Pinterest Ads","TikTok Business + TikTok Ads",Canva,"Google Analytics","ShipStation or Pirate Ship"}', '{"Maintaining consistent product photography style across a mixed catalog","Managing scent/ingredient FAQs and allergy sensitivities in product pages","Balancing small-batch uniqueness with the need for predictable availability","Creating short-form video that shows lather/texture without looking messy or low-end"}', '{"Bundle Lemon Soap with lemon-themed accessories for ‘Bathroom Refresh’ kits and gift sets","Run Pinterest-optimized listings/boards: ‘Lemon bathroom decor’, ‘Spring cleaning essentials’, ‘Teacher gifts’","TikTok UGC scripts: ‘What I’m putting in my guest bathroom’ and ‘Tiny luxuries under $20’","Limited-edition packaging (spring/summer) to drive urgency and repeat buys","Upsell: multi-pack for guest bathrooms, vacation rentals, and party favors"}', '2025-12-15 20:53:25.759+00', '2025-12-29 18:02:02.28732+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, '#EDEDED', '#FF6B6B', NULL, NULL, NULL, '498645dd-41d3-4e20-9f0c-291e130dafe3'),
	('a08f56a8-02ca-407e-b587-625fb2ae647b', 'Family Event & Party Planner Parent (Bulk Treat Buyer)', 'Parents organising kids’ birthdays, school holiday gatherings, and summer garden parties who need crowd-pleasing treats that are easy to serve and look great in photos. They value simple ingredients and a flavour everyone recognises (strawberry).', 'Consumer (Households / Events & Entertaining)', 'N/A (Household)', 'United Kingdom (England, Scotland, Wales—suburban and small-town communities)', '{"Party food planning is stressful; needs reliable crowd-pleasers to avoid waste","Concerns about artificial ingredients and parents’ expectations at kids’ parties","Limited freezer space—needs smart pack sizing and predictable storage","Timing issues: worries about melting and mess during serving","Hard to differentiate their party spread from everyone else’s"}', '{"Buy a freezer-ready treat that can serve 8–30 kids with minimal prep","Choose a ‘safe’ flavour for groups (strawberry) that most kids will accept","Provide a treat that feels more thoughtful and better-quality than standard party ice lollies","Create a visually fun party spread that photographs well for Instagram","Stay on budget while still offering something that feels special/modern"}', 'GBP £25–£80 per event for ice pops (depending on guest count and whether they buy extras for adults/siblings)', '{"Parent/Guardian (event organiser and purchaser)","Co-parent/Partner (budget approver)","Host child (influencer on theme and ‘cool’ factor)"}', '{Instagram,TikTok,"Facebook community groups",Pinterest,"Online grocery ordering (Tesco, Sainsbury’s, Asda, Morrisons)","Digital wallets (Apple Pay/Google Pay)"}', '{"Coordinating party-day logistics (storage, serving, keeping treats frozen)","Finding treats that satisfy both kids and other parents’ ingredient preferences","Ensuring enough quantity without overspending or overbuying"}', '{"Create ‘Party Pack’ bundles with clear serving guidance (e.g., 10/20/30 count suggestions)","Serve-and-share content: party table styling ideas featuring jazzy K‑pop-inspired packaging","Seasonal campaigns: summer birthdays, bank holiday gatherings, school holiday ‘garden party’","Offer reorder reminders and multi-buy incentives for repeat events across the season"}', '2026-01-24 14:43:57.04+00', '2026-01-24 14:43:57.04+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'fafe78e2-eb02-45f0-8666-3701bb5976f6'),
	('c0f7397e-715b-4951-9e26-b2f0c11c2c27', 'Bay Area Gut-Health Routine Builder', 'Health-conscious shopper who regularly buys functional beverages and supplements, is ingredient-driven, and wants an easy daily fermented drink that supports digestion without high sugar or artificial additives.', 'Consumer (Health & Wellness / Functional Beverages)', 'Individual consumer / Household (1–4 people)', 'United States — California (San Francisco Bay Area)', '{"Gets bloated after meals and wants a beverage-based solution that feels simpler than pills","Many ''healthy'' fizzy drinks are high in sugar or use sweeteners that upset digestion","Unclear probiotic/culture claims make it hard to trust fermented beverage labels","Hard to find a fermented drink that tastes good consistently across flavors","Worries about spending on products that don''t noticeably help after 2–3 weeks"}', '{"Reduce bloating and improve digestion with a consistent daily fermented drink routine","Replace sugary sodas/energy drinks with a low-sugar fizzy option that still feels like a treat","Choose products with transparent ingredients (live cultures, no artificial sweeteners/colors)","Find a gut-friendly beverage that fits into a workday (desk-friendly, easy to pack)","Subscribe or rebuy reliably without having to compare brands every time"}', 'USD $30–$80 per month for functional beverages (typical order value USD $25–$45; subscription acceptable if discounts apply)', '{"Primary grocery shopper","Health-conscious partner/spouse (influence)","Dietitian or wellness coach (occasional influence)"}', '{iPhone/Android,Instagram,Facebook,"Amazon (price comparison)",Instacart,"Apple Pay/Shop Pay","Email newsletters (Gmail)"}', '{"Maintaining consistency long enough to feel benefits without getting bored of flavors","Avoiding triggers like excess sugar, sugar alcohols, or dairy-based probiotic drinks","Finding credible education on what fermentation does vs. generic ''probiotic'' claims"}', '{"Ads and landing pages highlighting low sugar, live fermentation, and a 14-day routine","Bundle ''starter packs'' (variety flavors) with a subscribe-and-save option","Short-form content: ''bloat-friendly swaps'' and ''what to drink after meals'' on Instagram","Retargeting sequences focused on taste, ingredient transparency, and reviews from California customers"}', '2025-12-28 18:24:24.646+00', '2025-12-29 19:59:13.391972+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('416ce999-f601-4a68-8879-8478d4bafb6a', 'Eco-Conscious Specialty Subscription Seeker', 'An environmentally minded specialty-coffee drinker who wants a reliable monthly delivery of high-quality organic beans and actively prefers brands with authentic sustainability credentials (off-grid, low-impact roasting). They discover brands on Instagram and convert on a simple, trustworthy website.', 'Consumer (D2C) / Specialty coffee enthusiasts', 'Individual / household (1–3 coffee drinkers)', 'UK (England & Wales focus; rural towns and cities within standard delivery reach)', '{"Skepticism toward vague sustainability claims; wants proof of off-grid/low-impact practices and organic standards","Inconsistent freshness from supermarket beans or slow shipping that arrives stale","Difficulty choosing the right roast profile and grind size for their home setup","Subscription fatigue: complicated portals, hidden fees, hard-to-cancel services","Shipping waste (excess packaging) and uncertainty about recyclability/compostability"}', '{"Receive freshly roasted organic coffee on a predictable schedule (every 2–4 weeks) without running out","Reduce environmental impact by choosing a genuinely low-carbon, off-grid roasting brand vs. greenwashed alternatives","Find a go-to bean that matches their brew method (V60, AeroPress, espresso, cafetière) with consistent quality","Support small UK producers and feel confident the price reflects ethical sourcing and craft roasting","Easily manage subscription (skip, change grind size, change frequency) from a mobile-first website"}', '£18–£35 per month (typical 1–2 bags); willing to go up to £45/month for larger households or premium microlots', '{"Primary household shopper","Coffee enthusiast partner/spouse","Self (individual buyer)"}', '{Instagram,"Mobile web browsing (iOS/Android)","Apple Pay / Google Pay","Email (Gmail/Outlook)","Subscription management via website account"}', '{"Finding a coffee subscription that is both genuinely eco-led and consistently delicious","Understanding tasting notes and roast levels without jargon","Balancing cost with ethical priorities during higher cost-of-living periods"}', '{"Instagram Reels/Stories showcasing the off-grid Shropshire roastery, organic sourcing, and roasting days to build trust","Website quiz for brew method + flavor preference to recommend subscription options (frequency, grind, roast)","Packaging transparency page (materials, recycling instructions) and a simple sustainability proof section","Intro offer: first bag discounted or free shipping to reduce perceived risk","Retention: ‘skip/pause’ reminders and seasonal releases for variety without churn"}', '2025-12-14 19:34:46.65+00', '2025-12-23 12:33:04.48783+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, '#EDEDED', '#4D96FF', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('59992723-468c-40b8-a5f0-8857a0c2376d', 'SoCal Fitness Performance & Recovery Sipper', 'Fitness enthusiast (gym, running, cycling, yoga) who prioritizes recovery, hydration, and gut comfort. Buys functional beverages post-workout and responds to performance-oriented messaging and clean-label claims.', 'Consumer (Fitness / Active Lifestyle)', 'Individual consumer / Household (1–3 people)', 'United States — California (Los Angeles / Orange County / San Diego)', '{"Sports drinks and flavored waters feel too sweet, causing stomach upset during/after training","Many kombucha/fermented options taste too vinegary or inconsistent between batches","Unsure which fermented drinks actually help vs. ''wellness marketing''","Needs caffeine-free options for evening workouts without sleep disruption","Wants something fizzy that won’t derail nutrition goals (low calories/sugar)"}', '{"Support gut comfort while increasing protein intake and training volume","Find a carbonated alternative to sports drinks that isn''t sugar-heavy","Reduce post-workout stomach discomfort from pre-workout, protein shakes, or stress","Stick to a ''clean'' routine aligned with macros and ingredient standards","Have a convenient grab-and-go drink for gym bag, commute, or errands"}', 'USD $40–$120 per month (willing to pay USD $2.50–$4.50 per can/bottle; will subscribe if shipping is reliable in California)', '{"Individual buyer (athlete)","Personal trainer/coach (influence)","Gym community / friends (influence via social proof)"}', '{"Instagram Reels","Facebook Groups (local fitness communities)",Strava,"MyFitnessPal or Cronometer","Shopify-based DTC sites","Apple Pay/Google Pay","SMS offers"}', '{"Balancing taste with functional benefits (won’t repurchase if flavor is polarizing)","Attribution: hard to know if improved digestion comes from the drink or other routine changes","Keeping stocked without last-minute convenience-store purchases"}', '{"Position as ''post-workout fizzy gut support'' with clear nutrition callouts (low sugar, calories)","Creator partnerships with California-based trainers and run clubs","Workout-adjacent content: ''gut-friendly hydration stack'' and ''post-lift bloat fixes''","Offer multi-pack shipping and subscription cadence aligned with training schedules (weekly/biweekly)"}', '2025-12-28 18:24:24.744+00', '2025-12-29 19:59:13.391972+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('32f1a07e-e9d1-4722-b6f0-06fefc973c56', 'Nostalgia Collector (Millennial Nintendo Fan)', 'A 28–40 year-old Nintendo fan who grew up with NES/SNES/N64/GameCube and now buys authentic second-hand consoles and cartridges to rebuild a childhood collection, display it, and play original hardware.', 'Consumer Retail (B2C)', 'Individual consumer', 'United States (major metros and suburbs)', '{"Wasting money on counterfeit cartridges or reproduction shells that are hard to detect online","Receiving ''untested'' or partially working consoles (bad pins, failing lasers, controller drift) that require repairs","Incomplete listings that don’t show label condition, board authenticity, or clear photos of ports/serials","Overpaying due to price volatility and lack of trustworthy pricing benchmarks for vintage Nintendo items","Damage in transit (cracked cases, crushed boxes) due to poor packaging from individual sellers"}', '{"Find authentic, original Nintendo consoles (NES/SNES/N64/GameCube) that are tested and fully working","Buy specific childhood titles in original cartridge/disc format (not digital re-releases)","Complete a collection with matching region versions and original accessories (controllers, AV cables, power adapters)","Avoid counterfeits, reproduction cartridges, and mislabeled listings on marketplaces","Get fast, predictable shipping with tracking and careful packaging to prevent damage"}', '$75–$350 per month for games/accessories; $150–$450 per console purchase (occasionally up to $700 for bundles/rare items)', '{"Self (primary buyer)","Spouse/partner (for larger purchases)"}', '{"Facebook Marketplace","Facebook Groups (retro gaming, Nintendo collectors)",PayPal,"Shop Pay / Apple Pay","Google Search","PriceCharting (price research)"}', '{"Verifying authenticity from photos alone (labels, shells, screws, board indicators)","Finding bundles that include OEM accessories without paying inflated prices","Choosing between ''loose'' vs ''complete in box'' given condition and budget","Coordinating purchases around limited restocks and fast sell-through on Facebook"}', '{"Offer ''Authenticity-Checked'' badges with photo standards (front/back/board where applicable) and testing checklist","Create Facebook posts featuring weekly drops by console generation (e.g., ''N64 Friday'') to drive repeat visits","Sell curated bundles (console + 2 controllers + memory card + 3 classic games) with clear value vs piecemeal buying","Publish quick guides for buyers (how to spot repro cartridges, how to clean pins) to build trust and authority"}', '2026-01-08 21:21:18.347+00', '2026-01-08 21:21:18.347+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('5147cf62-9233-4906-a92a-989520f5e5d9', 'Primary-School Parent Seeking Dyslexia Clarity', 'A parent of a child aged 6–10 who is falling behind in reading/spelling and needs a formal dyslexia assessment with clear recommendations to take to the school and use at home.', 'B2C (Parents/Households)', 'Household (1–2 decision-making adults)', 'United Kingdom (England: West Midlands/Shropshire and surrounding counties)', '{"School says the child will ''catch up'' but the parent sees persistent difficulty with phonics, blending and reading fluency","Child avoids reading aloud, guesses words, and becomes upset or tired quickly during homework","Confusing mix of advice from teachers, tutors and online groups with no clear diagnosis","Parent is worried that the child is labelled ''lazy'' or ''not trying'' when effort is high","Long waits for local authority assessments; parent wants a quicker, credible route","Uncertainty about what evidence the school needs to implement interventions and adjustments"}', '{"Confirm whether dyslexia is the cause of slow reading progress, poor spelling and low confidence","Get a written report with practical classroom strategies to request reasonable adjustments from the school","Understand the child’s strengths (e.g., verbal reasoning) as well as difficulties to reduce shame and anxiety","Create an action plan for targeted support (e.g., phonics gaps, decoding, working memory) over the next term","Stop weekly battles over reading homework and rebuild the child’s willingness to read"}', 'GBP 350–900 for a full private assessment and report; GBP 50–150 per follow-up support session', '{Mother,Father/Co-parent,"Guardian (in some cases)"}', '{"Facebook groups for SEND/parent support","Meta Ads (Facebook/Instagram) as discovery channel","Google Search and Google Maps","School parent portal/apps (e.g., ParentPay/ClassDojo) for updates","Email and WhatsApp for booking/communication","Website booking/contact form"}', '{"Balancing assessment cost with other family commitments","Navigating school processes for SEN support and evidence requirements","Ensuring the child is comfortable and not anxious about being ''tested''","Coordinating with the class teacher/SENCO to share findings and implement recommendations"}', '{"Message around fast clarity + child-friendly assessment experience + practical next steps","Offer a free short pre-assessment call to confirm fit and reduce anxiety about the process","Create downloadable ''Questions to ask your school/SENCO'' checklist to capture leads","Retarget website visitors with testimonials and ''what’s included in the report'' explainer ads","Upsell a structured follow-up plan (e.g., 3-session parent coaching package) to implement strategies"}', '2026-01-29 22:01:28.006+00', '2026-01-29 22:01:28.006+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('dafa0864-49b5-4d0c-b4a3-b00d310159bb', 'Gift Buyer (Parent/Relative Buying Classic Nintendo)', 'A 30–55 year-old parent, aunt/uncle, or relative purchasing a vintage Nintendo console and age-appropriate games as a birthday/holiday gift or to share their childhood games with their kids.', 'Consumer Retail (B2C)', 'Household consumer', 'United States (suburban and family-dense regions)', '{"Not knowing which Nintendo console generation to choose (NES vs SNES vs N64 vs GameCube) for the recipient","Fear of buying something that won’t work on their TV or requires extra adapters they didn’t anticipate","Confusion over game ratings, content, and difficulty for kids","Concern about used items being dirty, damaged, or missing key components","Last-minute stress when listings don’t clearly state what is included in the box"}', '{"Buy a ready-to-play Nintendo setup that works out of the box (console + cables + controller + at least 1 game)","Get clear guidance on which console/game is suitable for a child’s age and interests","Ensure the purchase arrives on time for a birthday/holiday with reliable shipping and tracking","Avoid complicated setup, missing parts, and compatibility issues with modern TVs","Stay within a predictable gift budget without surprise add-ons"}', '$120–$350 per gift purchase; $25–$60 per additional game', '{"Parent/guardian (primary buyer)","Spouse/partner (approver for larger gifts)"}', '{Facebook,"Facebook Marketplace","Meta Pay / PayPal","Google Search","YouTube (setup/compatibility checks)"}', '{"Understanding what ''tested'' really means and what condition grades imply","Finding kid-friendly game bundles quickly without researching dozens of titles","Ensuring delivery timing and having a backup plan if inventory sells out","Navigating return/exchange policies if the gift isn’t a fit"}', '{"Create ''Gift-Ready Bundles'' with simple naming (e.g., ''N64 Starter Pack for Families'') and a checklist of what’s included","Offer a quick ''TV compatibility'' note per console and optional add-on adapters where relevant","Use Facebook ads targeting parents with creative that emphasizes ''tested, cleaned, ready-to-play'' and delivery timelines","Add a printable gift note/receipt option and straightforward exchange policy messaging"}', '2026-01-08 21:28:17.274+00', '2026-01-08 21:28:17.274+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('69ef8fa6-5d84-44b8-8847-2439a14863cd', 'Speedrunner/Retro Player (Performance-Focused Buyer)', 'A 18–35 year-old retro player who wants original Nintendo hardware for authentic gameplay feel, input latency, and community-accepted setups, buying specific consoles, controllers, and titles in working condition.', 'Consumer Retail (B2C)', 'Individual consumer', 'United States (college towns, tech hubs, and gaming communities)', '{"Controllers arriving with worn sticks/buttons that impact precision and times","Cartridges with dead save batteries or dirty contacts causing resets/freezes mid-run","Disc-based consoles with weak lasers leading to read errors and inconsistent performance","Listings that don’t specify revision/condition details relevant to serious players","Limited inventory causing missed chances to buy the exact model/accessory needed"}', '{"Get a reliable Nintendo console and OEM controller(s) that perform consistently (no stick drift, no button lag)","Buy specific cartridges/discs needed for practice runs and events (e.g., popular first-party Nintendo titles)","Minimize downtime by purchasing tested units with disclosed common failure points (pins, lasers, battery saves)","Optimize setup with the right cables/accessories to reduce display issues and maximize stability","Find reputable sellers with fast shipping so they can start practicing immediately"}', '$80–$250 per month for replacements/upgrades; $150–$500 for a console + controller setup; $30–$120 per game depending on title', '{"Self (primary buyer)"}', '{"Facebook Groups (speedrunning/retro communities)","Facebook Marketplace","Discord (community coordination)",PayPal,"Apple Pay","Google Sheets/Notion (tracking collections and practice needs)"}', '{"Finding OEM controllers in excellent condition at a fair price","Getting consistent hardware performance without needing repairs or modding","Identifying trusted sellers that understand enthusiast requirements","Balancing authenticity with practical setup needs for modern displays"}', '{"Offer ''Performance-Tested'' controller grading (stick range, button response) and disclose results in listings","Sell maintenance-ready items (fresh save battery replacement option, cleaned contacts) with clear add-on pricing","Run Facebook retargeting ads around restocks of high-demand items (OEM controllers, popular titles)","Create limited drops timed around weekends/events to capture urgent buyers who want fast practice setup"}', '2026-01-08 21:28:17.274+00', '2026-01-08 21:28:17.274+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('fb46d5dd-7e0c-4c2f-9f69-50e822cbf657', 'Coastal Lifestyle & Nautical Home Aesthetic Shopper', 'UK homeowner or renter who curates a coastal/nautical home vibe and likes coordinated, aesthetic products. Buys slippers for themselves as a daily comfort item and prefers designs that match their interior style (nautical theme, seaside artwork).', 'Consumer (B2C) - Lifestyle & Home', 'N/A (individual consumer)', 'United Kingdom (England: South West, South Coast; Wales coastal towns)', '{"Nautical-themed products often look novelty; wants tasteful design and quality","Indoor footwear can feel either comfy but ugly, or stylish but uncomfortable","Hard to assess sole grip for kitchen/wood floors from product pages","Some slippers lose shape quickly or look tatty after a few weeks","Unclear care instructions for keeping artwork looking fresh"}', '{"Own a pair of slippers that fits a coastal/nautical aesthetic without being childish","Get reliable comfort for daily indoor wear (quick on/off for busy home routines)","Choose a design that looks good in photos and when guests are around","Buy from a small brand with a clear story tied to seaside life","Replace worn-out slippers with something more distinctive and giftable"}', '£35–£65 per pair; £70–£120 per year for repeat purchases', '{"Self (buyer)","Household partner (shared household spending influence)"}', '{"Instagram Reels/Stories",Pinterest,"Google Search (brand + ‘nautical slippers’, ‘Cornish seaside slippers’)","Klarna/Clearpay (optional pay later)","Email newsletters for drops/restocks","Shopify checkout (or equivalent e-commerce)"}', '{"Balancing aesthetics with real durability and comfort","Finding a design that feels ‘British seaside’ while still modern","Knowing whether soles are suitable for indoor grip and light outdoor steps (bins/garden)","Understanding how to clean/maintain without damaging the artwork"}', '{"Lifestyle photography in coastal-style interiors and ‘morning routine’ content","Product page callouts for sole grip, materials, and care instructions","Limited edition seaside town artwork drops to drive repeat buying","Cross-sell with nautical-themed gift packaging and seasonal colourways","Retargeting ads highlighting comfort + tasteful design (not novelty)"}', '2026-01-24 15:02:56.204+00', '2026-01-24 19:40:16.442902+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('14956730-c82d-4e48-91d8-6417cacce1d1', 'London Vinyl & Cassette Collector (Age 28–45)', 'A serious music collector in London who actively buys rare/OG pressings and original hip-hop cassettes, values authenticity and condition grading, and regularly trades in duplicates to fund new finds.', 'Consumer (Music Collecting / Resale)', 'Individual', 'London, United Kingdom', '{"Fear of counterfeits/bootlegs and mislabeled pressings when buying vintage hip-hop","Inconsistent grading between sellers leading to returns or disputes","High shipping risk for fragile items (seam splits, warped vinyl, cassette shell damage) and poor packaging","Difficulty finding cassette-specific details (tape condition, dropouts, shell type, playback tested vs untested)","Prices fluctuate and sellers use vague descriptors that hide defects"}', '{"Find authentic first press/early press hip-hop records and original UK/US cassette releases with verifiable matrix/runout details","Buy confidently with consistent grading (sleeve/media), clear photos, and playback notes for noisy or worn items","Trade in duplicates and get fair valuation to reinvest into higher-tier pieces","Complete specific artist/label runs (e.g., early 90s hip-hop, underground UK hip-hop, DJ-centric releases) without overpaying","Secure protective storage and maintenance items (inner/outer sleeves, cleaning tools) to preserve collection value"}', 'GBP 100–400/month on records and cassettes; GBP 50–250 per high-priority item; up to GBP 800 for a rare grail pressing', '{"Collector (self)","Partner/spouse (secondary approver on larger purchases)"}', '{"Discogs (wantlist/collection tracking)","Instagram (crate-digging accounts and drops)","WhatsApp (purchase coordination and hold requests)","PayPal / Stripe (payments)","Spotify/Apple Music (discovery; cross-check releases)"}', '{"Validating authenticity quickly when items sell fast","Balancing budget between frequent smaller purchases and occasional grails","Storing and protecting media in small London flats","Coordinating pickups around work schedule"}', '{"Offer authenticated listings with runout/matrix photos and short audio clips for problem records","Create London pickup/drop days and reserved holds for repeat buyers","Launch collector bundles (genre/era packs) and condition-tiered pricing","Trade-in credit program with transparent grading and payout options","Membership/VIP early access to new arrivals and private drops"}', '2026-01-08 21:36:40.247+00', '2026-01-08 21:36:40.247+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '90fc1669-7feb-482e-a790-09b1321be725'),
	('f47b9a5b-7b8f-479b-ae64-7609e4bd8547', 'UK Remote Worker Seeking Comfort & Personality', 'UK-based professional working from home who wears slippers daily and wants comfort plus a bit of personality for their routine. Interested in a reliable slip-on that feels nicer than basic supermarket slippers, with Cornish seaside artwork as a conversation starter on casual video calls or social posts.', 'Consumer (B2C) - Remote Work & Everyday Comfort', 'N/A (individual consumer)', 'United Kingdom (major cities and commuter towns: Manchester, Birmingham, Bristol, Leeds, Glasgow, Edinburgh)', '{"Cheap slippers flatten quickly and cause foot fatigue during long days at home","Sweaty or overly warm slippers can be uncomfortable in centrally heated homes","Uncertainty whether the slippers will feel supportive enough for all-day wear","Fear of hassle if sizing is off and returns are slow","Hard to trust quality when product photos don’t show close-ups of stitching/print"}', '{"Upgrade daily WFH comfort with slippers that don’t look worn-out on day one","Have a slip-on option that’s quick between desk, kitchen, and door","Buy a design that feels uplifting and scenic (Cornish seaside town art) during long home days","Get a dependable fit to avoid return hassles","Receive fast UK delivery and transparent tracking"}', '£30–£60 per pair; £60–£100 for two pairs (one for home, one for travel/holiday cottage)', '{"Self (buyer)","Employer (occasional influencer only if buying via home-office wellbeing allowance)"}', '{"Google Search and Shopping ads","Instagram and TikTok (short-form product demos)","YouTube reviews (light touch)","Apple Pay/Google Pay","Gmail/Outlook for order confirmations","Parcel tracking via UK courier"}', '{"Finding slippers that remain supportive and comfortable for extended wear","Selecting the right warmth level for year-round UK indoor temperatures","Trusting the product will look as good in person as online","Avoiding time-consuming exchanges when busy with work"}', '{"Campaigns positioned around ‘WFH comfort upgrade’ with scenic, mood-lifting artwork","Short video creatives showing slip-on ease, flexibility, and close-up artwork detail","Clear comparison content: ‘Why these last longer than basic slippers’ (materials, construction)","Fast dispatch messaging and easy exchange flow to reduce purchase anxiety","Post-purchase email encouraging reviews/UGC with a ‘show your seaside view’ angle"}', '2026-01-24 15:02:56.317+00', '2026-01-24 19:40:16.442902+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('0b3d0210-85f3-4af6-a8ba-f8d614d734de', 'Boutique Parent Gift-Shop Owner (E-commerce + Local Pickup)', 'Owner-operator parent running a curated online gift shop (often with a small studio or local pickup). Stocks playful, aesthetic, scent-forward items for self-care, kids’ bathrooms, and small gifts; prioritizes photogenic products that perform on Pinterest and TikTok.', 'E-commerce Retail (Gifts, Bath & Body, Home Decor)', '1–5 employees', 'United States (suburban/metro areas with strong gift-buying demand)', '{"Struggles to find novelty soaps that are actually giftable (cute but not cheap-looking) and won’t melt/warp in shipping","Low conversion on “bath basics” because products look generic in product photos and don’t stand out in social feeds","Returns/complaints from fragrance expectations (too strong, too weak, not “fresh lemon”) affecting reviews","Needs packaging that feels premium and gift-ready without increasing fulfillment time","Inventory risk: buying too deep into a scent/theme that doesn’t sell after the initial social spike"}', '{"Add a low-risk, high-margin hero product that can be sold as a $12–$24 giftable add-on (lemon soap) with strong impulse appeal","Increase average order value via curated bundles (soap + lemon-themed bathroom accessory + small curiosity item)","Create seasonal drops that convert around spring cleaning, Mother’s Day, teacher gifts, Easter baskets, and summer hosting","Source products that photograph well and can be reliably restocked for repeat customers","Reduce customer acquisition costs by leaning into Pinterest search intent (bathroom refresh, lemon decor, gift ideas)"}', '$500–$2,500/month for inventory testing + $300–$1,500/month for content/ads (Pinterest/TikTok)', '{Owner/Founder,"Buyer/Merchandiser (often the owner)","Operations/Fulfillment Lead (part-time or contractor)"}', '{Shopify,Klaviyo,"Pinterest Business + Pinterest Ads","TikTok Business + TikTok Ads",Canva,"Google Analytics","ShipStation or Pirate Ship"}', '{"Maintaining consistent product photography style across a mixed catalog","Managing scent/ingredient FAQs and allergy sensitivities in product pages","Balancing small-batch uniqueness with the need for predictable availability","Creating short-form video that shows lather/texture without looking messy or low-end"}', '{"Bundle Lemon Soap with lemon-themed accessories for ‘Bathroom Refresh’ kits and gift sets","Run Pinterest-optimized listings/boards: ‘Lemon bathroom decor’, ‘Spring cleaning essentials’, ‘Teacher gifts’","TikTok UGC scripts: ‘What I’m putting in my guest bathroom’ and ‘Tiny luxuries under $20’","Limited-edition packaging (spring/summer) to drive urgency and repeat buys","Upsell: multi-pack for guest bathrooms, vacation rentals, and party favors"}', '2025-12-15 20:06:13.587+00', '2025-12-23 12:32:58.262686+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, '#EDEDED', '#6BCB77', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('557106e8-5fd2-4e24-939b-d98a54c4b4af', 'London DJ & Selector (Club/Radio) Seeking Vintage Media', 'A working DJ in London who uses vinyl and tapes for sets, radio shows, or mixtapes; needs reliable, playable copies, quick sourcing of specific cuts, and occasional equipment to maintain or digitise collections.', 'Entertainment (DJ / Radio / Events)', 'Self-employed / Micro-business (1–3)', 'London, United Kingdom', '{"Buying ''VG'' records that skip or have excessive surface noise under club sound systems","Limited time to dig—needs quick recommendations and holds for specific tracks","Hard to find cassette singles/mixtapes with confirmed playback quality","Equipment downtime (worn stylus, failing belts in cassette decks) causing missed prep time before gigs","Transporting records around London without damage"}', '{"Source clean, playable hip-hop and related genres on vinyl/cassette for sets (intro/outro friendly versions, instrumentals, acapellas when available)","Build themed crates fast (90s boom bap, UK hip-hop, golden era, underground) for upcoming gigs","Replace worn club-play copies with solid VG+/EX equivalents that cue well","Digitise select cassettes/vinyl for radio edits and archiving using reliable audio capture equipment","Get gear and accessories that reduce noise and improve playback (cartridges, stylus, slipmats, cleaning kits, cassette deck maintenance items)"}', 'GBP 200–700/month on records and cassettes; GBP 150–600/quarter on equipment/accessories; up to GBP 1,200 for critical playback/recording gear', '{"DJ/Artist (owner)","Radio show producer (influencer for purchases tied to broadcast needs)","Event promoter (influencer for set requirements)"}', '{"Rekordbox/Serato (library management; even if playing vinyl, for prep)","Discogs (sourcing and price checks)","Bandcamp/SoundCloud (discovery and references)","Instagram/TikTok (gig promos and music discovery)","WhatsApp (quick sourcing, holds, pickup coordination)"}', '{"Ensuring consistent audio quality across old pressings and tapes","Last-minute gig changes requiring rapid crate adjustments","Finding trustworthy sellers for high-rotation records","Maintaining playback equipment without specialist support"}', '{"Curated DJ-ready drops (battle breaks, instrumentals, clean pressings) with skip-tested grading notes","Same-day London pickup and emergency replacement service for key records","Bundled accessories with purchases (sleeves, cleaning supplies, stylus care) targeted to DJs","Trade-in program for worn duplicates with discount toward cleaner copies","Workshops/pop-ups: vinyl care, tape digitisation, equipment maintenance basics"}', '2026-01-08 21:36:40.394+00', '2026-01-08 21:36:40.394+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '90fc1669-7feb-482e-a790-09b1321be725'),
	('7d4e847f-3a09-4209-9e2b-a7ab5d21b259', 'London Boutique Retailer/Studio Buying Vintage Stock & Playback Gear', 'A small London-based record shop, lifestyle boutique, barbershop, café, or creative studio that sells or displays curated vintage records/cassettes and needs reliable playback equipment to create an authentic in-store vibe and incremental sales.', 'Retail / Hospitality / Creative Studio', 'Small business (2–15)', 'London, United Kingdom', '{"Unpredictable quality when buying job lots—too many unplayable or badly graded items","Time cost of individually sourcing and verifying vintage media","Need for invoices/receipts and clear stock lists for accounting","Equipment reliability issues in a commercial environment (heavy use, customer handling)","Storage and merchandising constraints in small London spaces"}', '{"Buy curated batches of vintage hip-hop records and cassettes that match the brand aesthetic and customer demographics","Maintain a rotating in-store selection with predictable margins and minimal dead stock","Source dependable playback/hi-fi equipment for ambience and occasional in-store events (listening sessions, DJ nights)","Offer giftable items (classic albums, mixtapes, limited curated packs) to increase average order value","Avoid reputational risk by ensuring items are authentic and accurately graded"}', 'GBP 500–2,500/month for stock replenishment; GBP 300–2,000 for playback equipment per setup; up to GBP 5,000 for a full in-store audio refresh (turntable, amp, speakers, accessories)', '{Owner/Founder,"Store Manager","Studio Manager/Creative Director (influencer for curation and vibe)","Bookkeeper/Finance admin (approver for larger purchases)"}', '{"Shopify/Square (POS and inventory)","Instagram (merchandising and drops)","WhatsApp/Email (B2B ordering and stock lists)","Discogs (pricing benchmarks and catalog checks)","Google Sheets (stock intake and grading notes)"}', '{"Keeping curated stock aligned with seasonal footfall and local trends","Managing returns/complaints if grading isn’t consistent","Balancing display-worthy items with affordable impulse buys","Coordinating deliveries and secure storage for valuable items"}', '{"Wholesale/consignment partnerships with pre-sorted, theme-based bundles and clear grading","Subscription-style monthly curation box for in-store rotation (e.g., 30 records + 20 cassettes)","Provide commercial-grade playback packages with setup support and maintenance add-ons","Co-branded events: listening nights, crate-digging pop-ups, in-store drops","Offer authentication notes and story cards (label/era/context) to increase perceived value and conversion"}', '2026-01-08 21:36:40.491+00', '2026-01-08 21:36:40.491+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '90fc1669-7feb-482e-a790-09b1321be725'),
	('8621be5e-a81b-4044-89b7-f9fd4a35c396', 'Year 6–Year 9 Parent Concerned About Dyscalculia and Maths Anxiety', 'A parent of a child aged 10–14 who struggles with number sense, times tables, mental maths and word problems; the child may have strong reading skills but escalating maths anxiety and falling attainment.', 'B2C (Parents/Households)', 'Household (1–2 decision-making adults)', 'United Kingdom (England and Wales; families willing to travel within region for assessment)', '{"Child memorises procedures but cannot retain facts; panics under timed conditions","Tutoring has been ongoing but progress is slow and inconsistent, causing frustration","School feedback is vague (''needs more practice'') with no explanation of why practice isn’t sticking","Child struggles with time, money, and multi-step word problems in everyday life","Parent worries about long-term impact on science subjects and career options","Uncertainty about what qualifies as dyscalculia versus ''not liking maths''"}', '{"Identify whether dyscalculia is contributing to persistent difficulties with maths despite tutoring","Get a clear profile of gaps (e.g., number bonds, place value, working memory, processing speed) to target support","Secure exam access arrangements evidence where appropriate (e.g., extra time) for upcoming tests/GCSE pathway","Reduce maths anxiety and rebuild confidence before secondary school sets/streaming decisions","Stop spending money on generic tuition that doesn’t match the child’s learning profile"}', 'GBP 450–1,050 for dyscalculia-focused assessment and report; GBP 60–180 per specialist support session', '{Mother,Father/Co-parent,Guardian,"Sometimes involved: Step-parent contributing financially"}', '{"Facebook and Instagram (Meta) for discovery","Meta Ads lead forms or website enquiry","Google Search (e.g., ''dyscalculia assessment near me'')","Email for sending documents and report delivery","Zoom/Google Meet for parent feedback sessions (if offered)","Online calendar booking (via website)"}', '{"Differentiating dyscalculia from general gaps caused by disrupted schooling","Keeping the child engaged during assessment when confidence is low","Aligning recommendations with what the school can realistically implement","Managing expectations around quick fixes versus structured intervention over time"}', '{"Campaigns focused on ''maths anxiety + number sense'' rather than only the label dyscalculia","Offer a post-assessment parent roadmap (what to do in 30/60/90 days) to increase perceived value","Partnership referrals from independent tutors who suspect dyscalculia","Create ads timed around transition points (Year 6 SATs, Year 7 settling, GCSE option planning)","Provide a concise ''school summary page'' to help parents advocate effectively with SENCOs"}', '2026-01-29 22:01:28.006+00', '2026-01-29 22:01:28.006+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('f975870f-85a5-4a76-b398-b9074336f5b0', 'Premium Home Wok Enthusiast (Direct-to-Consumer)', 'Home chefs who cook 4–7 nights/week and want a forever-quality, handmade cast iron wok for high-heat searing, stir-fries, and one-pan meals. They follow cooking creators and buy premium cookware online when they see proof (results, durability, seasoning performance).', 'E-commerce (DTC cookware) / Home cooking', 'Solo consumer / household', 'United States, Canada, United Kingdom, Australia (metro/suburban)', '{"Nonstick woks/pans scratch, degrade, and can’t handle sustained high heat without failing","Thin carbon-steel woks warp on electric/induction or develop uneven heat zones","Unsure which wok size is truly big enough for 3–6 servings without crowding and steaming food","Confusion about seasoning and maintenance; fear of rust or sticky seasoning","Buying cookware online feels risky without clear proof of weight, handle comfort, and heat performance"}', '{"Get restaurant-quality stir-fry and sear at home using a super size wok without warping or hot spots","Own a single ''buy-it-for-life'' wok that replaces multiple pans and works for family-sized portions","Cook with high heat and develop a reliable seasoning layer that becomes more nonstick over time","Find a wok that feels stable and safe to handle when tossing food (balanced weight, secure handle)","Improve weeknight cooking speed: one-pan meals with fast cleanup and fewer dishes"}', '$150–$350 one-time purchase; will pay up to $450 for a handmade, lifetime-quality wok with accessories', '{"Primary home cook","Spouse/partner (shared household budget)"}', '{Instagram,TikTok,"Shopify store checkout","Apple Pay / Google Pay","Klaviyo (email/SMS)","Afterpay/Klarna (buy-now-pay-later)"}', '{"Educating on cast iron wok benefits vs carbon steel (heat retention, durability) without scaring people about weight","Overcoming maintenance objections (seasoning, cleaning) and fear of ''high effort cookware''","Showing real cooking outcomes on common home setups (gas, electric coil, glass-top, induction with adapter)"}', '{"TikTok/IG Reels series: ''Super Size Wok Weeknight'' (5 meals, 15 minutes each) demonstrating sear and portion capacity","Proof-driven creative: side-by-side comparisons (thin wok vs cast iron) showing warping, heat retention, and crust formation","Bundled starter kit: wok + seasoning wax/oil + metal spatula + care card to reduce maintenance anxiety","UGC program with home cooks showing first 30 days of seasoning progression and cleanup routines"}', '2025-12-16 22:15:01.449+00', '2025-12-17 11:11:56.888693+00', 'bf859676-aeb9-40f5-a5fa-77e55cf0df90', NULL, '#FFE69B', '#4D96FF', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('af854d89-077f-48d1-a8eb-3498890a7be0', 'Cooking Creator / Culinary Educator (Influencer + Workshop Host)', 'Recipe creators, cooking teachers, and culinary educators who publish frequent short-form video content. They want cookware that looks premium on camera, performs reliably for repeated shoots, and helps them produce visually striking ''sizzle'' moments and family-sized recipes.', 'Creator economy / Culinary education / Affiliate e-commerce', 'Solo creator to small team (1–5)', 'English-speaking markets; high concentration in US/UK/CA/AU', '{"Cookware that looks cheap on camera or performs inconsistently ruins takes and wastes time","Nonstick cookware can’t deliver the crust/sear visuals that drive engagement and credibility","Frequent filming accelerates wear; pans warp or seasoning becomes inconsistent across shoots","Audience asks about tools; without a clear story (handmade, cast iron, built-to-last) conversions are weak","Limited storage/space: creators prefer one versatile hero piece over many specialized pans"}', '{"Produce high-heat, visually compelling content (sizzle, steam, sear) that performs on TikTok/Instagram","Differentiate with a signature pan/tool that viewers remember and ask about in comments","Film family-style, big-batch recipes in a single vessel (super size wok) to reduce cuts and complexity","Generate affiliate/brand partnership income from cookware recommendations","Maintain consistent results across repeated takes without pan warping or coating degradation"}', '$0–$800 per collaboration (product seeding to paid); $200–$500 for personal cookware purchases; $1,000–$5,000 for multi-video campaigns with usage rights', '{Creator/Host,"Talent Manager/Agent (if represented)","Producer/Editor (small team input on visuals and workflow)"}', '{Instagram,TikTok,"CapCut / Adobe Premiere","Link-in-bio (Linktree/Beacons)","Shopify Collabs / affiliate platform","Google Analytics / platform insights"}', '{"Aligning product messaging (handmade cast iron saucepan maker + super size wok) into a simple, repeatable creator narrative","Ensuring content demonstrates practical benefits quickly (first 2 seconds hook) rather than long explanations","Managing creator concerns about weight/handling on camera and audience objections about maintenance"}', '{"Creator kit: talking points, seasoning quick-start, and 3 ''viral-ready'' recipes optimized for short-form (e.g., smash fried rice, chili crisp noodles, steak stir-fry)","Offer exclusive creator discount codes and affiliate commission to drive trackable sales","Run a ''30-day seasoning journey'' challenge with creators to normalize upkeep and build trust","Whitelisting/UGC ads: repurpose best-performing creator clips into paid TikTok/IG campaigns for scalable acquisition"}', '2025-12-16 22:15:01.449+00', '2025-12-17 11:13:48.889787+00', 'bf859676-aeb9-40f5-a5fa-77e55cf0df90', NULL, '#EDEDED', '#6BCB77', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
	('647d92f4-7253-4bac-aafd-bb6adddfdac0', 'Millennial Parents Preserving Early Childhood Memories', 'Busy parents who have thousands of baby/toddler photos on phones and cloud albums and want a professionally crafted digital movie that tells the family story (first year, birthdays, milestones) without spending weekends editing.', 'B2C / Household Consumers', 'N/A (individual/family buyer)', 'United States — California (Bay Area, Sacramento, Central Valley)', '{"Overwhelmed by huge camera roll and can’t curate the “best” photos without second-guessing","Tried editing apps but results look generic, time-consuming, and inconsistent with family vibe","Deadlines sneak up (birthday party in 2 weeks) and they don’t have time to learn editing","Wants music that feels emotional but worries about copyright or awkward song choices","Partner coordination friction: disagreements about which photos to include and how long it should be"}', '{"Turn 200–1,000 scattered phone photos into a 3–8 minute digital movie with a clear beginning-middle-end storyline","Create a shareable keepsake for grandparents and close friends (private link + downloadable file)","Have a polished movie ready for a specific date (1st/2nd/3rd birthday, Mother’s Day/Father’s Day, preschool graduation)","Include captions (names, dates, milestone text) so the story is understandable without narration","Reduce decision fatigue by having someone else select the best photos and sequence them"}', 'USD $250–$600 per family story package', '{"Mom (primary organizer and buyer)","Dad/Partner (approver of spend and final cut feedback)"}', '{"iPhone/Android camera","Google Photos and/or Apple Photos","Facebook and Facebook Groups (local parenting groups)","Instagram (optional sharing destination)","Dropbox/Google Drive for file transfer"}', '{"Providing organized photo batches with dates and basic context (names/events) quickly","Selecting photos that are high enough quality for a cinematic feel","Ensuring timeline accuracy across multiple phones and shared albums"}', '{"Facebook targeting: new parents, parents of toddlers, birthday party planners, family-focused interests in California","Seasonal campaigns: Mother’s Day, Father’s Day, end-of-year recap, back-to-school, preschool graduation","Add-ons: extra length, multiple versions (short social cut + full cut), subtitles/captions, photo cleanup","Referral loops: grandparents or friends request their own after seeing the movie"}', '2026-01-08 22:01:22.364+00', '2026-01-08 22:01:22.364+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'a72f7a2b-71f4-469c-b8fc-4ab4a2c3420a'),
	('68176f5a-4b96-4526-97c4-aa41272b11da', 'Adult Children Creating Tribute Films for Parents/Grandparents', 'Adults organizing meaningful digital tribute movies from decades of family photos for milestone birthdays, anniversaries, celebrations of life, or retirement events—often coordinating with siblings and extended family.', 'B2C / Household Consumers', 'N/A (individual/family buyer)', 'United States — California (Los Angeles, Orange County, San Diego)', '{"Photos are scattered across relatives, texts, emails, Facebook uploads, and boxes of prints","Limited time to scan/organize before an anniversary party or memorial service","Emotional load: wants it perfect and worries about leaving someone out","Inconsistent photo quality (faded scans, low-res screenshots) makes DIY editing frustrating","Need help choosing pacing, music tone, and transitions to avoid feeling cheesy"}', '{"Create a heartfelt 5–12 minute tribute movie combining old scanned photos and newer smartphone images","Present the movie at an event (projector/TV-ready) and also share a private link with family","Include clear chaptering (childhood, marriage, kids, grandkids, vacations) and on-screen dates/locations","Coordinate photo submissions from siblings/cousins without chaos","Deliver a piece that feels respectful and cinematic, not like a slideshow template"}', 'USD $500–$1,200 per tribute story package', '{"Adult child organizer (project lead and payer)","Siblings (influencers/approvers of content and tone)","Event host (influencer on runtime and format requirements)"}', '{"Facebook (family groups, event pages, Messenger)","Google Drive/Dropbox for collecting submissions","Smartphone scanning apps (e.g., photo scan apps)","Email and iMessage/SMS for coordination","Smart TV/Projector playback (MP4 file delivery)"}', '{"Getting relatives to submit photos on time and with captions/years","Managing sensitive family dynamics and choosing inclusive photo sets","Ensuring final video format plays smoothly at the venue"}', '{"Facebook ads around life events: anniversaries, retirements, milestone birthdays, memorial planning","Partnership/referrals with event planners, funeral homes, celebration-of-life venues in California","Upsells: scanning/cleanup service, voiceover from family, multiple cut-down versions for sharing","Fast-turnaround package for urgent timelines (7–10 days)"}', '2026-01-08 22:01:22.364+00', '2026-01-08 22:01:22.364+00', 'b9f43ab4-a714-432a-843f-4b6bb6ef3891', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'a72f7a2b-71f4-469c-b8fc-4ab4a2c3420a'),
	('a6ebea85-ddf4-40f4-9da4-c5961abb0451', 'Grandparents Commissioning Legacy Movies for the Whole Family', 'Grandparents who value family history and want a legacy-style digital movie that preserves decades of memories, organizes photos into a coherent story, and can be gifted to children/grandchildren.', 'B2C / Household Consumers', 'N/A (individual/family buyer)', 'United States — California (Palm Springs, Ventura County, Monterey, Santa Rosa)', '{"Boxes of printed photos and albums with no organization or labeling","Wants a professional result but doesn’t want to learn editing software","Concerned that family history will be lost as older relatives age","Not sure which photos matter most or how to structure the story","May feel intimidated by digital file transfers and formats"}', '{"Create a legacy movie that documents family roots, major milestones, and traditions across generations","Give a meaningful gift to adult children/grandkids for holidays, reunions, or milestone birthdays","Digitize and include older printed photos and albums in a modern, easy-to-watch format","Ensure the movie includes names, dates, and locations so future generations understand the context","Have a finished video file that can be shared privately and stored safely for the long term"}', 'USD $400–$900 per legacy family story package', '{"Grandparent (primary buyer)","Adult child (technical helper and co-approver)","Spouse/Partner (approver and contributor of photos)"}', '{"Facebook (to see family posts and message relatives)",Email,"Smartphone camera for capturing prints if scanning isn’t available","USB drive and/or Google Drive/Dropbox for delivery","Smart TV/tablet for viewing"}', '{"Collecting and digitizing older printed photos without damaging originals","Providing accurate timelines (years, locations, names) for captions","Navigating upload/download steps and reviewing drafts comfortably"}', '{"Facebook targeting: grandparents, family reunion interest, genealogy/family history 