	('a2fef360-8488-4726-930e-a7eaa3918eec', 'Family Food Planner (Local Quality Seeker)', 'Busy parent or household organiser who wants reliable, tasty sausages made from locally reared UK meat for quick midweek dinners and weekend breakfasts, and prefers buying from trusted local producers discovered via Facebook.', 'Consumer (Household)', 'N/A (Individual/Household)', 'United Kingdom (England: West Midlands, Staffordshire, Worcestershire)', '{"Supermarket sausages shrink, split, or leak fat in the pan, making dinners messier and less appealing","Confusion about meat origin and how animals were raised; distrust of vague labels","Not enough time to shop around; needs straightforward ordering and collection/delivery info from Facebook","Worries about wasting money if the family doesn’t like a new flavour"}', '{"Find dependable locally reared UK meat sausages for fast family meals that still feel wholesome","Reduce reliance on supermarket meat by switching to a local producer with transparent sourcing","Keep weekly meal planning simple with products that work across multiple recipes (pasta, traybakes, casseroles, breakfasts)","Make sure picky eaters enjoy meals by choosing consistent flavour and texture"}', '£20–£45 per purchase (weekly/fortnightly), up to £80 for BBQ/party top-ups', '{"Primary grocery shopper (parent/guardian)","Household budget holder"}', '{"Facebook (Groups, Marketplace, Messenger)","Instagram (optional, for food inspiration)","Apple Pay/Google Pay (where available)","WhatsApp (sometimes used for local ordering updates)"}', '{"Coordinating collection times around school runs and work","Balancing desire for higher-quality meat with a tight household grocery budget","Finding kid-friendly flavours without overly processed ingredients"}', '{"Facebook posts featuring ''family favourites'' bundles (e.g., classic pork + mild herb + chipolatas) with cooking time tips","Clear provenance messaging: locally reared, where sourced, what’s in the sausage (no fille