	('e666668e-4b8a-460c-8db4-63296f9c5855', 'Freelance Creative on a Capsule Wardrobe', 'A West Coast freelance creative who wants affordable, distinctive outfits for client meetings, shoots, and remote work content, and discovers style ideas primarily on Pinterest before buying on a website.', 'Freelance / Creative services (design, photo/video, marketing, content)', '1 (self-employed)', 'United States — West Coast (Seattle, Portland, San Francisco, Los Angeles)', '{"Fast fashion feels disposable and doesn’t hold up for frequent wear or content shoots","Hard to find unique pieces in local stores without spending entire weekends browsing","Sizing uncertainty and fit anxiety when buying secondhand online","Wants outfits that look intentional on camera but doesn’t want to overpay for ‘vintage’ markup","Overwhelmed by too many choices; wants curated edits rather than endless scrolling"}', '{"Build a small capsule wardrobe of 15–30 versatile pieces that photograph well for personal branding","Find comfortable, unique clothing for hybrid life (home office + coffee meetings + events)","Shop consciously by choosing secondhand/old clothes over fast fashion while staying on-trend","Use Pinterest boards to plan outfits by season and buy specific ‘look’ components","Keep spend predictable while refreshing style for new gigs or social events"}', 'USD 80–300/month on secondhand clothing (or USD 150–600 per seasonal refresh)', '{"Individual Buyer (Freelancer)","Partner/Spouse (occasionally influences purchase)"}', '{Pinterest,Instagram,"Shopify-based websites","Apple Pay / Google Pay",Gmail,"Notion or Google Keep for outfit planning"}', '{"Determining accurate fit from measurements and photos","Finding pieces that match a consistent personal brand aesthetic","Shopping efficiently with limited time between projects","Avoiding impulse buys that don’t integrate into a capsule wardrobe"}', '{"Create Pinterest-first ‘shop the look’ collections with clear sizing and styling notes","Offer