	('aa3b1cb3-7fcf-4008-8961-192a797c4649', 'Local Foodie & Farmers’ Market Regular (Provenance-First)', 'Ingredient-focused shopper who actively seeks locally reared UK meat, values craft and provenance, and is willing to pay more for flavour, texture, and transparent sourcing; engages with producers on Facebook for updates, stall locations, and new product drops.', 'Consumer (Food & Drink Enthusiast)', 'N/A (Individual/Household)', 'United Kingdom (Scotland: Glasgow, Edinburgh, Stirling)', '{"Frustration with vague marketing claims like ''farm-style'' without real sourcing details","Inconsistent quality from some local stalls; wants a producer they can trust repeatedly","Limited visibility of stock levels and where/when to buy each week","Needs detailed ingredient lists for dietary preferences (e.g., lower sugar, no unnecessary fillers)"}', '{"Buy sausages made from locally reared UK meat with clear provenance and minimal unnecessary additives","Discover unique flavours and limited batches that feel artisan rather than mass-produced","Support small local producers and recommend them to friends/community groups","Build a reliable rotation of high-quality proteins for home cooking"}', '£25–£60 per purchase, 2–4 times per month; up to £100 for seasonal hampers/gift buys', '{"Primary buyer (foodie/home cook)","Gift purchaser (for birthdays/seasonal presents)"}', '{"Facebook Pages (product updates, pinned posts for locations)","Facebook Groups (local food and farmers’ market communities)","Email (optional for pre-order lists if offered)","Card/contactless payments"}', '{"Planning purchases around market days or limited production runs","Verifying animal welfare and sourcing claims without long-form content","Transporting chilled goods when combining multiple market stops"}', '{"Provenance storytelling posts: farm/source highlights, batch notes, and behind-the-scenes production content on Facebook","Pre-order system promoted via Facebook with weekly ''available this week'' posts to reduce uncertainty","Tasting notes and pairing suggestions (mustards, ales, sides) to match foodie interests","Giftable bundles and seasonal packs marketed ahead of holidays with clear collection dates"}', '2026-01-29 13:36:42.546+00', '2026-01-29 13:36:42.546+00', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '75414dc9-89fb-4060-b0eb-8e3922b7a948'),
	('b11554cc-14e4-408d-9007-5696989039f6', 'High-Achieving Child With Hidden Difficulties (Twice-Exceptional Profile)', 'A parent of a child aged 8–16 who appears bright but is underperforming relative to ability due to slow processing, poor spelling/handwriting, fatigue, or inconsistent attainment; parent wants an in-depth assessment to explain the discrepancy and guide targeted support.', 'B2C (Parents/Households)', 'Household (1–2 decision-making adults)', 'United Kingdom (UK-wide; typically higher-income families seeking private assessment)', '{"Teachers say the child is capable but ''careless'' or ''rushing''—parent suspects underlying processing/learning issue","Homework takes disproportionately long; child is exhausted and emotionally reactive after school","Spelling and writing quality lag behind verbal reasoning and general knowledge","Child can explain concepts aloud but struggles to show work on paper or under timed conditions","Parent worries the child is developing perfectionism, avoidance, or school refusal","Previous informal screenings were inconclusive; parent wants a comprehensive, credible assessment"}', '{"Explain the gap between verbal ability and written output (e.g., slow writing, poor spelling, messy work)","Get evidence-based recommendations for school adjustments (e.g., assistive technology, reduced copying, extra time)","Prevent burnout and protect self-esteem as academic demands increase","Clarify whether dyslexia/dyscalculia is present even when grades are ''fine''","Obtain a professional report suitable for independent school support plans and exam arrangements documentation"}', 'GBP 650–1,400 for comprehensive assessment and detailed written report; GBP 75–250 for follow-up consultation or school liaison (if offered)', '{Mother,Father/Co-parent,"Sometimes: Grandparent providing financial support"}', '{"Facebook/Instagram for discovery and remarketing","Meta Ads targeting parents by interests (education, tutoring, SEND support)","Website