house types with colour suggestions (e.g., black on red brick; grey on modern render; brown/cream on traditional)."}, {"cta": "Get the leaf grid suitability checklist by email.", "hook": "If you’re clearing gutters every autumn, this is for you.", "name": "Leaf Grid ‘Near Trees’ Lead Magnet", "angle": "Target homes near trees: explain when leaf grid works, what it won’t solve, and how to avoid overflow."}, {"cta": "Get a quote range in 24 hours (photo-based).", "hook": "See the difference in one day.", "name": "Before/After Proof + Testimonial Retarget", "angle": "Simple before/after images with short homeowner quotes focused on leak reduction and less maintenance; capture leads via email form."}], "success_metrics": {"kpis": ["Audit requests (email leads) per week", "Lead-to-survey/quote conversion rate", "Quote-to-install conversion rate", "Cost per lead (Meta)", "Average time from lead to booked install"], "targets": ["6–12 qualified leads in 30 days (with £0–£500 spend)", "30–50% of leads provide required photos/details within 48 hours", "20–35% of qualified leads progress to a formal quote/survey", "£15–£40 cost per lead on Meta (small-budget benchmark)", "Reply/response time: under 1 business day for new leads"]}}', 'icp_strategy_v2_brand_context', 'gpt-5.2', '2026-04-15 16:15:58.343+00', '2026-04-15 19:08:11.975+00', 'The OG'),
	('43427016-6e4d-4e82-8d4f-eaf1390d1bf8', 'b11554cc-14e4-408d-9007-5696989039f6', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', 'Generate qualified leads', NULL, NULL, NULL, '{"offer": {"lead_magnet_idea": "Checklist: ‘Signs of dyslexia and processing difficulties in bright children (8–16)’ + ‘What to track for school’ mini worksheet.", "recommended_offer": "Free 10–15 minute parent suitability call + paid comprehensive assessment with written report (priced within £650–£1,400), plus optional follow-up/school liaison call (£75–£250).", "landing_page_sections": ["Who this assessment is for (clear signs + age range)", "What you’ll learn (strengths, barriers, adjustments, next steps)", "What’s included (sessions, tests, report, turnaround)", "How it helps at school (adjustments, access arrangements support)", "Pricing band + what affects price (age, complexity, add-ons)", "Process and timings (from enquiry to report)", "FAQs (grades fine, labels, child anxiety, school pushback)", "Enquiry form + call booking link"]}, "ad_assets": {"headlines": ["Bright child, slow writing? Get clarity", "Dyslexia signs even when grades are ‘fine’", "When verbal ability doesn’t show on paper", "Stop the ‘careless’ label with evidence", "Assessment + school-ready recommendations"], "primary_texts": ["If your child can explain it brilliantly but struggles to get it down on paper, a comprehensive assessment can pinpoint what’s going on and what to do next. Download the checklist and learn the common hidden barriers.", "Teachers say ‘capable but rushing’? Homework takes hours? We help you understand the ability–attainment gap and get practical adjustments for school. Book a short parent call.", "Bright children can mask difficulties until workload increases. Get a clear picture of strengths, barriers and priority recommendations to protect confidence and reduce burnout."], "creative_briefs": ["Checklist lead ad: simple graphic with 5–7 signs; promise ‘clear next steps for home and school’.", "Carousel: ‘What you see’ vs ‘What it can mean’ (e.g., messy writing → processing speed/coordination load) with CTA to enquiry.", "Testimonial-style quote cards (generic): focus on reduced homework time, better adjustments, improved confidence; include ‘book a call’ CTA."]}, "messaging": {"value_props": ["Explain the discrepancy between talking ability and written output (speed, spelling, handwriting, working memory)", "Identify or rule out dyslexia/dyscalculia and related processing factors", "Provide practical adjustments: extra time, reduced copying, assistive tech, marking guidance", "Reduce homework battles and fatigue by targeting the real bottleneck", "Increase confidence by framing difficulties as specific, solvable barriers"], "pain_to_promise": ["‘They’re bright but careless’ → Pinpoint the specific skills and processing load causing errors", "Homework takes hours → Identify the time-sinks and give a shorter, smarter plan", "Exhausted and emotional after school → Recommend workload/stamina adjustments to prevent burnout", "Great verbally, weak on paper → Provide evidence and strategies to bridge oral-to-written performance", "School not taking it seriously → Supply a clear report and suggested wording for school meetings"], "objections_and_rebuttals": ["‘But their grades are fine’ → Bright children can compensate; early identification prevents secondary issues (anxiety, avoidance, burnout).", "‘Will this label them?’ → The goal is not a label; it’s clarity and targeted support that reduces stress.", "‘We already did a screening’ → Screenings can miss complex profiles; a full assessment looks at the pattern across skills and impact.", "‘It’s too expensive’ → The report can unlock effective adjustments and reduce ongoing tutoring/strain; offer staged options (assessment + optional follow-up).", "‘My child will resist’ → Use child-friendly framing: “finding the easiest way for your brain to show what it knows”, with choice and reassurance."]}, "positioning": {"why_us": "Parents need a credible explanation for an ability–attainment gap plus clear, prioritised next steps that schools can act on, even when grades look ‘fine’.", "one_liner": "Comprehensive learning and processing assessments for bright children whose written work and stamina don’t match their verbal ability—so parents can secure the right adjustments and protect confidence.", "differentiators": ["Twice-exceptional lens: strengths and barriers explained together", "Action-first reporting: clear top recommendations for home and school", "School-ready documentation: wording that supports exam access arrangements and support plans", "Parent advocacy support: optional follow-up call and school-facing summary letter template"]}, "channel_plan": {"first_14_days": ["Create/refresh one core landing page: ‘Assessment for bright children with hidden learning difficulties’ with enquiry form and clear pricing band.", "Build 6–10 FAQs addressing ‘grades are fine’, exam access arrangements, what happens in an assessment, turnaround times, and child anxiety.", "Set up Meta lead ad offering checklist; connect to automated email (3 emails over 7 days) ending with booking CTA.", "Launch a small Google Search campaign on 8–15 keywords (slow processing, dyslexia assessment, processing speed, exam access arrangements) to the same landing page.", "Add retargeting (Meta) to website visitors with 2 simple ads: case story + ‘book a call’."], "primary_channel": "Google Search (SEO + high-intent Google Ads)", "secondary_channels": ["Facebook/Instagram (Meta lead ads + retargeting)", "Email (lead nurture and booking)", "Website conversion optimisation (service page + FAQs)"]}, "campaign_ideas": [{"cta": "Download the checklist", "hook": "Is your bright child’s written work lagging behind what they can say?", "name": "Ability–Attainment Gap Checker (Meta lead ad)", "angle": "Lead magnet checklist + short email sequence explaining common hidden barriers (processing speed, working memory, dyslexia indicators) and next steps."}, {"cta": "Book a call / Enquire", "hook": "Comprehensive assessment for bright children with slow, messy or exhausting written work", "name": "Google Search: ‘Dyslexia in bright child’ + ‘slow writing’ intent capture", "angle": "High-intent search ads to a service page with ‘what you’ll learn’ framework and report outcomes."}, {"cta": "Request assessment availability", "hook": "From 2-hour homework to 45 minutes (with the right adjustments)", "name": "Parent case-story carousel (organic + retargeting)", "angle": "Generic, anonymised “before/after” story focused on confidence, workload and school changes."}, {"cta": "Get the toolkit", "hook": "What to say when school says ‘they’re just careless’", "name": "School meeting toolkit", "angle": "Short guide + template phrases that link observed issues to reasonable adjustments."}], "success_metrics": {"kpis": ["Website enquiry conversion rate", "Cost per lead (Meta)", "Cost per enquiry (Google)", "Booked suitability calls per week", "Assessment bookings per month"], "targets": ["Landing page conversion: 3–7% from high-intent traffic", "Meta lead CPL: £8–£25 (checklist)", "Google cost per enquiry: £40–£120 (dependent on competition)", "Show rate for calls: 70%+ with reminders", "30-day outcome: 8–20 qualified enquiries (adjust to budget and capacity)"]}}', 'icp_strategy_v2_brand_context', 'gpt-5.2', '2026-04-16 08:08:06.082+00', '2026-04-16 08:08:06.082+00', 'Strategy 1'),
	('cef4daf2-5e6c-4317-8b3b-881f613000ed', 'b11554cc-14e4-408d-9007-5696989039f6', '155ee0b1-3a3c-4a24-a836-14ddafc0f3b5', 'Generate qualified leads', NULL, NULL, NULL, '{"offer": {"lead_magnet_idea": "Checklist: ‘Hidden signs of dyslexia/processing difficulties in bright children (8–16)’", "recommended_offer": "Free 15-minute parent suitability call + ‘2e ability–attainment gap’ checklist download (lead magnet).", "landing_page_sections": ["Problem snapshot (bright, verbal, but written output lags)", "Who it’s for (ages 8–16; common signs)", "What the assessment covers (strengths, barriers, impact, recommendations)", "What you get (PDF report, prioritised plan, optional follow-up/school summary)", "Pricing range and next steps (call → booking)", "FAQs (will school accept it? will it label my child? timelines)"]}, "ad_assets": {"headlines": ["Bright but struggling to write?", "Why homework takes so long", "Dyslexia in bright children", "Processing speed assessment (UK)", "Evidence for extra time/exam access"], "primary_texts": ["Your child can explain it brilliantly—but on paper it’s slow, messy or stressful. A comprehensive assessment can clarify what’s getting in the way and what to ask school to change.", "If teachers say ‘capable but careless’, it may be processing speed, working memory, spelling or handwriting—not effort. Get a clear explanation and practical adjustments.", "Grades can look ‘fine’ while your child is exhausted and losing confidence. Find the hidden barrier early and protect self-esteem as demands increase."], "creative_briefs": ["Meta carousel: 4 panels—‘Talks it through’ → ‘Struggles on paper’ → ‘Homework takes hours’ → ‘Get clarity + school-ready recommendations’. CTA to checklist.", "Static image: simple checklist visual with 6 signs (slow writing, poor spelling, fatigue, inconsistent results, avoids timed work, perfectionism). CTA to download.", "Google RSA: emphasise ‘UK-wide’, ‘comprehensive report’, ‘school adjustments’, ‘exam evidence’ with sitelinks to FAQs/pricing/contact."]}, "messaging": {"value_props": ["Understand why your child can talk it through but struggles to show it on paper", "Get clear answers on dyslexia/dysgraphia/dyscalculia traits even when grades look ‘fine’", "Reduce homework battles by matching support to the real barrier (speed, working memory, motor, spelling)", "Walk away with a prioritised plan for school and home, not just scores"], "pain_to_promise": ["Teachers say ‘careless’ or ‘not trying’ → Identify the specific processing or learning bottleneck and how to accommodate it", "Homework takes hours → Recommendations that reduce workload friction and fatigue", "Bright verbally, weaker on paper → Explain the discrepancy and protect self-esteem", "School not taking it seriously → Provide credible documentation and suggested wording for adjustments/exams"], "objections_and_rebuttals": ["‘My child isn’t failing—do we need this?’ → Early clarity prevents burnout and helps keep learning enjoyable as demands increase.", "‘Won’t a label harm confidence?’ → A good assessment reframes it as ‘how your brain works’ and gives practical fixes that reduce shame.", "‘School won’t act anyway.’ → The report focuses on reasonable adjustments and provides a simple summary you can share with SENCO/teachers.", "‘We’ve done a screening already.’ → Screenings miss complex profiles; a full assessment maps strengths, barriers and impact in real tasks."]}, "positioning": {"why_us": "We focus on explaining the ability–attainment gap with clear, evidence-based findings and a parent-friendly report that translates into actionable next steps for home and school.", "one_liner": "Comprehensive learning and processing assessment for bright children whose written output, stamina or speed doesn’t match their ability—so parents can secure practical school adjustments and protect confidence.", "differentiators": ["Strengths-first, twice-exceptional (2e) lens: clarifies both high ability and hidden barriers", "Report written to be usable: prioritised recommendations and exam-access-arrangements-friendly wording", "Practical school adjustment toolkit (assistive tech, reduced copying, extra time, marking approaches)", "Optional parent advocacy support (follow-up call, school-facing summary/letter template)"]}, "channel_plan": {"first_14_days": ["Build one landing page: ‘Bright child, struggling with writing/speed’ with enquiry form and FAQs", "Create 2–3 Google Search ad groups: dyslexia assessment, processing speed, exam access arrangements evidence", "Set up Meta lead ad for the checklist + thank-you email delivering PDF", "Write a 4-email sequence: (1) what the gap can mean (2) school adjustments (3) what an assessment includes (4) how to book", "Add a simple retargeting ad to push warm traffic to a call/booking form"], "primary_channel": "Google Search (high intent) + a single focused landing page", "secondary_channels": ["Facebook/Instagram lead ads (checklist)", "Email nurture (3–5 emails)", "Retargeting on Meta to site visitors/lead openers"]}, "campaign_ideas": [{"cta": "Take the 2-minute check", "hook": "If your child is bright but writing is slow, messy or exhausting, you’re not alone.", "name": "Ability–Attainment Gap Quiz", "angle": "Short on-site self-check leading to tailored next step (call/assessment)."}, {"cta": "Get the free checklist", "hook": "‘Signs of dyslexia in bright children’ checklist", "name": "Checklist Lead Magnet (Meta)", "angle": "Meta Lead Form to email PDF + nurture sequence to consultation."}, {"cta": "Book a discovery call", "hook": "From 2-hour homework to 45 minutes (with the right adjustments)", "name": "Case Study Carousel (Meta/IG)", "angle": "Before/after stories focused on confidence and practical changes."}, {"cta": "Check availability", "hook": "Extra time, word processor, reduced copying—what evidence is needed?", "name": "Google Search: Exam Access Arrangements", "angle": "Search ads to a focused landing page for parents of Y5–Y11."}], "success_metrics": {"kpis": ["Qualified lead volume (enquiry + call booked)", "Lead-to-call booking rate", "Call-to-assessment conversion rate", "Cost per lead (Meta) / cost per enquiry (Search)", "Show rate for calls"], "targets": ["8–20 qualified enquiries in 30 days (depending on capacity)", "20–35% landing page to enquiry/call", "40–60% call-to-booking for suitable cases", "Meta CPL within £8–£25 for checklist leads", "Call no-show rate under 15%"]}}', 'icp_strategy_v2_brand_context', 'gpt-5.2', '2026-04-16 08:08:41.357+00', '2026-04-16 08:08:41.357+00', 'Strategy 2');
INSERT INTO "public"."icp_meta_activation_packs" ("id", "icp_id", "user_id", "strategy_id", "pack_name", "goal", "pack_json", "prompt_version", "model", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES
	('16b4d1c3-ca82-41c6-a703-647fd058fcfe', '205b7ea1-5db2-4b18-85b3-f319d38da55a', '3d065808-3338-43b1-8bfd-50660bbf83e5', '284d3611-97d7-46a6-8026-77081d8ab156', 'Meta Activation Pack 1', 'Build a practical Meta audience and campaign roadmap', '{"roadmap_30d": [{"week": "Week 1", "focus": "Tracking, assets, and audience foundations", "tasks": ["Confirm Meta Pixel/dataset is installed on all pages and firing correctly (PageView, ViewContent; add Lead on form submission/thank-you where possible).", "Set up/refresh Custom Audiences listed above in Ads Manager (website, engagement, lead forms, customer lists).", "Create exclusion audiences (customers, recent leads, quote thank-you visitors) and apply them consistently.", "Prepare seed files: Completed installs (365–730D) and Qualified leads (180–365D); deduplicate and standardise email/phone formatting.", "Build a simple landing page or quote page section clarifying: seamless vs sectional, colour options, leaf grid option, downpipe compatibility, and the quote/survey process.", "Creative sprint: produce 6–10 core creatives (before/after, colour swatches on real homes, leaf grid demo, ‘what’s included’ checklist, testimonial tiles, rain leak problem/solution video)."], "checkpoint": "Events show in Events Manager; audiences populating; seed files ready with acceptable match rate.", "decision_rule": "If key events aren’t tracking or audiences aren’t populating, fix tracking before scaling spend."}, {"week": "Week 2", "focus": "Launch initial campaigns and creative testing", "tasks": ["Launch Prospecting campaign with 1% LAL (completed installs) and 2% LAL as separate ad sets; add 3–5% LAL for scale if budget allows.", "Launch Retargeting campaign with: High-intent pages 30D, Website all 30D, Video viewers 60D, Engagers 365D (separate ad sets if volume allows).", "Launch Lead recovery ad set: Lead form openers not submitted 30D with simplified form and click-to-WhatsApp option.", "Set up a basic naming convention (Campaign: UK | Objective | Audience | Creative angle) and ensure UTMs are applied for analytics.", "Implement a lead quality feedback loop: tag leads by outcome (booked survey, quoted, won/lost, out-of-area) in your CRM/spreadsheet."], "checkpoint": "First 50–100 leads or meaningful click volume; confirm lead notifications and response time workflow (email/WhatsApp/calls).", "decision_rule": "If lead quality is poor, tighten geo targeting to service areas, add clearer price range messaging, and increase form qualification (property type, postcode, access notes) without adding sensitive questions."}, {"week": "Week 3", "focus": "Optimisation based on lead quality and on-site behaviour", "tasks": ["Review breakdowns (placements, age bands, geo by region) and reallocate budget to best-performing ad sets/creatives.", "Rotate in new creatives: colour-match confidence (real installs), ‘connect to existing downpipes’ cost-saving angle, and leaf grid ‘less cleaning’ demo.", "Introduce retargeting sequencing: 0–7D high-intent gets strongest CTA; 8–30D gets testimonials/FAQs; 31–60D gets seasonal hook (rain/leaf fall) if applicable.", "Improve landing page/form based on questions from leads (add FAQs: disruption, timing, access constraints, warranty/aftercare, downpipe options).", "Upload refreshed lead/customer lists and regenerate lookalikes if seed size has grown."], "checkpoint": "Lead-to-survey rate improving; cost per qualified lead stabilising; retargeting frequency not excessive.", "decision_rule": "If retargeting frequency is high with low conversions, shorten windows or expand warm pools (video views, engagement) and refresh creatives."}, {"week": "Week 4", "focus": "Scale winners and formalise a repeatable system", "tasks": ["Scale budget gradually (e.g., 15–30% every 48–72 hours) on the best-performing 1% and retargeting ad sets.", "Test Advantage+ placements and/or Advantage+ Audience with strong exclusions, keeping a controlled ‘benchmark’ ad set live for comparison.", "Create a structured monthly creative cadence: 2 new before/after sets, 1 leaf grid demo, 1 colour-focused reel, 2 testimonial tiles.", "Build a ‘proof library’: organise photos by colour, house type, and problem solved (leaks, overflow staining, tired gutters).", "Document SOPs: lead response time, quote process messaging, when to suggest connecting to existing downpipes vs upgrading, and post-install review request workflow.", "Plan next month experiments: separate lookalikes by seed type (customers vs qualified leads), test click-to-WhatsApp vs Instant Form, and test offer framing (‘No more painting’ vs ‘Leak-free after heavy rain’)."], "checkpoint": "Clear set of winning audiences, creatives, and a target CPL/CPQL benchmark; consistent lead handling process.", "decision_rule": "Only scale ad sets that meet your qualified lead KPI for 7+ days; pause or rebuild anything driving persistent low-quality/out-of-area enquiries."}], "seed_quality": {"minimum_size": "Aim for 300+ matched users for initial testing; if smaller, start with 1% LAL only and expand once volume grows.", "recommended_size": "1,000–5,000 records per seed (refresh monthly); split by recency (0–90D, 91–365D) if large enough.", "do_not_use_cohorts": ["Website visitors as the only seed (too broad) unless you restrict to very high intent pages.", "All leads including unqualified/spam records.", "Old customer lists (3+ years) if product/price/coverage has changed materially.", "Any dataset collected without appropriate notice/consent or without a lawful basis for advertising use."], "data_quality_checklist": ["Use one row per person; deduplicate by email/phone.", "Normalise UK phone numbers (include country code where possible) and remove spaces.", "Lowercase and trim emails; remove obvious typos where confirmed.", "Include only people within service coverage (UK; optionally filter to the regions you actually serve).", "Prefer recent data: weight or segment by last 180–365 days to reflect current pricing/offer.", "Exclude leads with no contactability (missing both email and phone).", "Exclude poor-fit enquiries where known (e.g., non-residential, out-of-area, ‘price-only’ spam).", "If possible, create separate seeds: (A) completed installs, (B) survey booked, (C) quote accepted—keep each seed ‘pure’."], "primary_seed_definition": "Completed installs (customers) in the last 365–730 days, UK only, with at least one strong identifier (email and/or phone) and consistent formatting; exclude commercial/non-residential jobs if present.", "fallback_seed_definition": "Qualified quote requests in the last 180–365 days where the lead reached a meaningful stage (e.g., booked survey, received quote, or confirmed suitable property type), UK only."}, "audience_plan": [{"use_case": "Warm retargeting to move users from research to quote request.", "build_rule": "Include: All website visitors in last 30 days. If volume is low, extend to 60–180 days.", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Leads/Quote Submitted (thank-you page) – 180D", "Exclude: Customers/Completed installs list – 365D (if available)"], "source_type": "Meta Pixel / dataset (Website Custom Audience)", "audience_name": "Website visitors (All) – 30D", "retention_window": "30 days (scale to 60–180 if needed)"}, {"use_case": "Conversion-focused retargeting with strong offer/CTA (book survey/get quote).", "build_rule": "Include visitors to key intent URLs such as /quote, /contact, /pricing, /leaf-grid, /colours, /seamless-aluminium vs /upvc, /downpipes in last 30 days.", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Leads/Quote Submitted – 180D", "Exclude: Recent customers list – 365D"], "source_type": "Meta Pixel / dataset (Website Custom Audience)", "audience_name": "High-intent pages – 30D (Pricing/Quote/Leaf Grid/Colours)", "retention_window": "30 days"}, {"use_case": "Retarget people who are actively comparing options; test testimonials, before/after, warranty/aftercare messaging.", "build_rule": "If available in your setup: include top engaged visitors (e.g., highest time on site or multiple page views) in last 30 days. If not available, approximate by combining visitors to 2+ key pages (e.g., Colours + Leaf Grid, or Colours + Quote).", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Leads/Quote Submitted – 180D", "Exclude: Customers list – 365D"], "source_type": "Meta Pixel / dataset (Website Custom Audience)", "audience_name": "Time on site / engaged visitors – 30D", "retention_window": "30 days"}, {"use_case": "Warm retargeting with a ‘Get a fixed price quote’ or ‘Book a survey’ CTA.", "build_rule": "Include people who watched at least 25% of your videos (before/after, rain leak demo, colour showcase) in last 60 days.", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Leads/Quote Submitted – 180D", "Exclude: Customers list – 365D"], "source_type": "Engagement Custom Audience (Video)", "audience_name": "Meta video viewers – 25%+ watched – 60D", "retention_window": "60 days"}, {"use_case": "Low-cost warm pool; good for social proof, UGC-style creatives, and seasonal rain/leaf-fall messaging.", "build_rule": "Include anyone who engaged with your Facebook Page or Instagram professional account (profile visits, post/ad engagement, saves, DMs) in last 365 days.", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Leads/Quote Submitted – 180D", "Exclude: Customers list – 365D"], "source_type": "Engagement Custom Audience (Page + Instagram account)", "audience_name": "Instagram/Facebook engagers – 365D", "retention_window": "365 days"}, {"use_case": "Recover drop-offs with simpler form, click-to-WhatsApp, and ‘what’s included’ clarifiers.", "build_rule": "Include: people who opened your Instant Form in last 30 days. Exclude: people who submitted the form in last 180 days.", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Instant Form submissions – 180D", "Exclude: Customers list – 365D"], "source_type": "Lead Ads Custom Audience (Instant Form engagement)", "audience_name": "Lead form openers but not submitted – 30D", "retention_window": "30 days (submission exclusion 180 days)"}, {"use_case": "Appointment/survey booking, quote follow-up, reassurance content (colour confidence, downpipe compatibility, aftercare/warranty).", "build_rule": "Include: people who submitted your Instant Form in last 180 days. Split into 0–7D, 8–30D, 31–180D if volume allows.", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Customers list – 365D"], "source_type": "Lead Ads Custom Audience (Instant Form submissions)", "audience_name": "Lead form submitters – 180D (nurture/booking)", "retention_window": "180 days"}, {"use_case": "Seed for lookalikes; upsell aluminium downpipes/leaf grid where appropriate; request reviews/referrals (separate campaign).", "build_rule": "Upload hashed identifiers (email/phone) for customers with completed installs in last 365 days; include only records with marketing consent where required.", "exclusions": ["Exclude from acquisition campaigns to avoid wasting budget"], "source_type": "Customer list (first-party data upload)", "audience_name": "Customer list (Completed installs) – 365D", "retention_window": "Up to 365 days (refresh monthly)"}, {"use_case": "High-quality seed for lookalikes; also for retargeting with ‘book survey’ and objection-handling creatives.", "build_rule": "Include people who requested a quote (submitted web form, Instant Form, or tracked Lead event) in last 180 days. If using list: include only leads with valid contact details and within serviceable UK areas.", "exclusions": ["Exclude: Completed installs list – 365D (for acquisition)"], "source_type": "Customer list upload OR Pixel events (Lead/CompleteRegistration)", "audience_name": "Quote requests (Qualified leads) – 180D", "retention_window": "180 days"}], "lookalike_plan": {"location_note": "Create lookalikes in the United Kingdom. If you only service specific regions, apply location targeting at ad set level (people living in the selected areas) to avoid out-of-area leads.", "source_audiences": ["Customer list (Completed installs) – 365D", "Quote requests (Qualified leads) – 180D", "Lead form submitters – 180D (only if quality is good)"], "stacking_strategy": "Keep lookalikes separate at ad set level initially (1%, 2%, 3–5%) to control budget and read performance. Once you have clear winners, you can consolidate 1%+2% or run Advantage+ Audience using the best seed signals, while retaining exclusions.", "mandatory_exclusions": ["Exclude: Customer list (Completed installs) – 365D", "Exclude: Lead form submitters – 180D (for prospecting)", "Exclude: Website quote thank-you page visitors – 180D (where tracked)"], "tier_recommendations": [{"use_case": "Primary prospecting; best efficiency and lead quality. Use with strongest proof (before/after, testimonials, warranty) and a clear quote CTA.", "tier_name": "High similarity", "percentage": "1% (UK)"}, {"use_case": "Scale once 1% is stable; test broader angles like colour-match confidence and ‘connect to existing downpipes’.", "tier_name": "Balanced scale", "percentage": "2% (UK)"}, {"use_case": "Higher volume; use for creative testing and top-of-funnel education (seamless vs sectional, leaf grid benefits). Expect lower conversion rate; manage with exclusions and tighter lead qualification.", "tier_name": "Scale", "percentage": "3–5% (UK)"}]}, "compliance_notes": ["Use only first-party customer/lead data collected with appropriate notice and a lawful basis for marketing/advertising; honour opt-outs and suppression lists.", "When uploading customer lists, ensure data is securely handled, minimised (only necessary fields), and kept up to date; use hashing via Meta’s upload workflow.", "Do not target or infer sensitive traits in ads or audience definitions (including health, finances, housing status, employment, ethnicity, religion, sexuality). Keep targeting based on engagement/intent and lawful first-party data.", "Be transparent in your privacy policy about use of Meta Pixel/datasets and remarketing; provide cookie consent where required in the UK.", "Avoid misleading guarantees; only state warranty/finish lifespan claims you can substantiate in writing and apply consistently across ads and landing pages.", "If using WhatsApp/call ads, ensure you have a compliant process for consent and record-keeping for follow-up marketing."], "messaging_matrix": [{"audience": "3–5% Lookalike (UK) + broad home improvement interest signals (optional)", "pain_angle": "Heavy rain exposes joint leaks and overflowing gutters that stain walls and damage landscaping.", "proof_type": "Before/after photos + simple explainer graphic (seamless vs sectional joints)", "primary_cta": "Learn more / Get a quote", "funnel_stage": "Top of funnel", "promise_angle": "Seamless aluminium runs reduce joint-related leaks; tidy finish that lasts.", "awareness_level": "Problem-aware (leaks/overflow)", "creative_format": "15–30s video + carousel of before/after + headline-led image"}, {"audience": "1% Lookalike (Completed installs) – UK", "pain_angle": "Tired, mismatched gutters and repeated repairs are false economy.", "proof_type": "Customer testimonial + close-up colour finish shots", "primary_cta": "Request a quote", "funnel_stage": "Top to mid funnel", "promise_angle": "Powder-coated aluminium in classic colours with 30+ year finish expectancy—no repainting.", "awareness_level": "Solution-aware (considering replacement)", "creative_format": "Carousel (colour options) + testimonial static + short UGC-style video"}, {"audience": "Website visitors (All) – 30D", "pain_angle": "Unsure what’s included and whether it will connect to existing downpipes.", "proof_type": "Checklist ‘What’s included’ + install timeline + compatibility note", "primary_cta": "Book a survey / Get quote", "funnel_stage": "Mid funnel", "promise_angle": "Clear quote options: connect to existing downpipes or upgrade to new aluminium pipes; straightforward survey and install plan.", "awareness_level": "Considering options", "creative_format": "Static checklist image + 20s talking-head/explainer video"}, {"audience": "High-intent pages – 30D (Colours/Leaf Grid/Quote)", "pain_angle": "Wants confidence on colour choice and maintenance reduction before committing.", "proof_type": "Short case study: ‘before (overflow) → after (clean lines)’ + review snippet", "primary_cta": "Message on WhatsApp / Call now / Get quote", "funnel_stage": "Bottom of funnel", "promise_angle": "Colour-match confidence (swatches + real homes) and optional leaf grid to reduce cleaning.", "awareness_level": "Most-aware (ready to act)", "creative_format": "Click-to-WhatsApp ad + reels-style before/after + image with colour swatches"}, {"audience": "Lead form openers not submitted – 30D", "pain_angle": "Form friction / uncertainty about price, disruption, or access constraints.", "proof_type": "‘3 steps’ graphic + FAQs (access, conservatories, narrow side passages)", "primary_cta": "Finish your quote request", "funnel_stage": "Bottom of funnel", "promise_angle": "Fast, no-obligation quote with a simple 3-step process; we handle tricky access where possible.", "awareness_level": "Most-aware but hesitant", "creative_format": "Single image + short FAQ video + Instant Form with fewer fields"}, {"audience": "Lead form submitters – 0–7D", "pain_angle": "Wants quick scheduling and clarity on next steps.", "proof_type": "Process timeline + installer credibility (years, guarantee wording if applicable)", "primary_cta": "Confirm your appointment", "funnel_stage": "Post-lead nurture", "promise_angle": "Confirm survey slot, outline timing, aftercare and warranty expectations.", "awareness_level": "Converted to lead", "creative_format": "Click-to-call / WhatsApp + simple timeline creative"}]}', 'meta_activation_pack_v1', 'gpt-5.2', '2026-04-15 20:24:43.679+00', '2026-04-15 20:24:43.679+00');
INSERT INTO "public"."icp_social_content_packs" ("id", "icp_id", "user_id", "strategy_id", "pack_name", "goal", "channel_mix", "pack_json", "visuals_generated_count", "prompt_version", "plan_model", "visual_model", "created_at", "updated_at") VALUES
	('de18a7b9-ad19-4340-80b7-f1d1bb3eef42', '205b7ea1-5db2-4b18-85b3-f319d38da55a', '3d065808-3338-43b1-8bfd-50660bbf83e5', '284d3611-97d7-46a6-8026-77081d8ab156', 'Social Content Pack 1', 'Build a 30-day social campaign to generate qualified leads', '{Instagram}', '{"items": [{"id": "leak-free-assurance-post", "cta": "Book your FREE leak inspection today!", "hook": "Say goodbye to leaky gutter joints once and for all!", "type": "post", "week": "Week 1", "concept": "Show close-up imagery of seamless aluminium gutter joints with water tests proving no leaks.", "objective": "Raise awareness of leak-free benefits", "caption_long": "Stop worrying about leaks ruining your home''s walls and foundations. Our seamless aluminium gutters eliminate troublesome joints, providing a reliable, leak-free solution that protects your home, rain or shine.", "repurpose_to": ["Meta Ads", "Email"], "caption_short": "Tired of leaks after heavy rain? Our seamless gutters seal every joint.", "creative_brief": "Visual: Close-up dynamic image of seamless gutter with water flowing smoothly; text overlay highlighting ''No leaks at joints''; warm, trust-building colours."}, {"id": "maintenance-free-living-carousel", "cta": "Discover our maintenance-free options now.", "hook": "Imagine gutters that never need repainting or messy cleaning.", "type": "carousel", "week": "Week 2", "concept": "Multi-slide visuals showing faded uPVC gutters vs. vibrant seamless aluminium, plus added leaf grids preventing debris build-up.", "objective": "Educate on low upkeep benefits", "caption_long": "Our seamless aluminium gutters come in durable colours guaranteed for over 30 years — no repainting needed. Add a leaf grid to block leaves and reduce risky cleaning sessions. Make gutter upkeep effortless.", "repurpose_to": ["Meta Ads"], "caption_short": "Enjoy gutters that stay looking fresh and stay clear of leaves all year.", "creative_brief": "Slide 1: Old vs new gutters comparison; Slide 2: Leaf grid installing preventing debris; Slide 3: Colour range showcase; consistent branding and informative icons."}, {"id": "colour-match-confidence-carousel", "cta": "Browse colour options and get inspired today.", "hook": "Choose your perfect gutter colour to enhance your home’s style.", "type": "carousel", "week": "Week 3", "concept": "Slides presenting before and after shots of homes with gutter upgrades in various colours that complement brickwork and fascias.", "objective": "Showcase design and colour matching", "caption_long": "Transform your home’s look with seamless aluminium gutters available in black, brown, white, cream, green, and grey. Our powder-coated finish ensures lasting beauty that complements your brickwork and fascias perfectly.", "repurpose_to": ["Email"], "caption_short": "Match your gutters perfectly with our selection of 6 stunning colours.", "creative_brief": "Each slide features a home exterior before and after with text mentioning colour names; include swatches and installation images for visual appeal."}, {"id": "downpipe-compatibility-reel", "cta": "Book your installation consultation now.", "hook": "Worried about connecting new gutters to existing downpipes? We’ve got you covered.", "type": "reel", "week": "Week 4", "concept": "Short video walkthrough showing how seamless guttering interfaces with old or new downpipes in various colours and styles.", "objective": "Explain connection and installation options", "caption_long": "Whether you want to keep your existing downpipes or upgrade to new aluminium ones, we ensure a clean, colour-coordinated finish with minimal disruption and expert installation. Leave gutter worries behind.", "repurpose_to": ["Facebook", "Meta Ads"], "caption_short": "Seamless connection to old or new downpipes, colour-matched for your home.", "creative_brief": "Video: Installer demonstrating connections with voiceover and on-screen text highlighting no-mess, quick fit, and colour matching."}, {"id": "customer-testimonial-post", "cta": "Read more testimonials and get your quote today.", "hook": "See why UK homeowners trust MC Seamless Guttering to protect their homes.", "type": "post", "week": "Week 4", "concept": "Photo of happy customers beside their upgraded seamless gutters with a short testimonial quote.", "objective": "Build trust through social proof", "caption_long": "‘Our new aluminium gutters have transformed our home – no leaks, less cleaning, and great colour match. The MC Seamless team made installation simple!’ – Sarah & Tom, England", "repurpose_to": ["Instagram Stories", "Email"], "caption_short": "Trusted by homeowners across the UK for reliable, beautiful guttering.", "creative_brief": "Photo of real customers with pleasant home backdrop; overlay quote text; brand colours and logo; warm inviting tone."}, {"id": "leaf-grid-benefits-reel", "cta": "Ask about leaf grid installations today.", "hook": "Stop dangerous gutter cleaning with our leaf grid solution.", "type": "reel", "week": "Week 2", "concept": "Dynamic footage showing leaf grid installation and gutters free of leaves despite surrounding trees.", "objective": "Demonstrate leaf grid advantage", "caption_long": "Avoid tedious and unsafe gutter cleaning. Our specialised leaf grids prevent debris build-up, letting rainwater flow freely. Protect your home effortlessly and enjoy peace of mind.", "repurpose_to": ["Facebook"], "caption_short": "Keep your gutters clean and safe with our durable leaf grids.", "creative_brief": "Video combines installation shots, close-up of grids blocking leaves, and flowing water graphics with upbeat music."}, {"id": "quick-installation-carousel", "cta": "Schedule your installation today.", "hook": "Get new seamless gutters installed efficiently with minimal fuss.", "type": "carousel", "week": "Week 4", "concept": "Series of images or graphics depicting the installation process, from prep to final inspection, emphasising speed and cleanliness.", "objective": "Highlight quick, low-disruption instal", "caption_long": "Our expert team completes seamless gutter installations promptly while keeping disruption to your household to a minimum — all backed by aftercare and warranty for your full peace of mind.", "repurpose_to": ["Meta Ads", "Email"], "caption_short": "Fast, clean installation that respects your home and schedule.", "creative_brief": "Slides: preparation, installation teams at work, finishing details, and smiling homeowner; highlight quick turnaround and care."}, {"id": "protect-home-post", "cta": "Protect your home — get a free assessment today.", "hook": "Prevent damp and staining that damage your home’s brickwork and landscaping.", "type": "post", "week": "Week 1", "concept": "Visual of damaged walls from overflowing gutters contrasted with protected home after upgrade.", "objective": "Highlight protection from damp and damage", "caption_long": "Overflowing or leaking gutters cause damp patches, rot, and ruined landscaping. Our seamless aluminium gutters ensure water flows safely away, safeguarding your home and garden for decades.", "repurpose_to": ["Instagram Stories"], "caption_short": "Stop water damage before it starts with professional seamless guttering.", "creative_brief": "Split image with damaged and protected home; strong messaging emphasizing prevention; use reassuring brand colours."}, {"id": "why-seamless-reel", "cta": "Watch and learn more on our website.", "hook": "Why choose seamless aluminium gutters? Here’s what you need to know.", "type": "reel", "week": "Week 1", "concept": "Engaging animated explainer video highlighting joint-free runs, durability, colour options, and leaf grid compatibility.", "objective": "Explain seamless gutter benefits concisely", "caption_long": "No leaks. No repainting. Less cleaning. Seamless aluminium gutters are designed for longevity and curb appeal, giving your home protection and style with minimal fuss.", "repurpose_to": ["Meta Ads"], "caption_short": "Discover why seamless gutters are the best choice for UK homes.", "creative_brief": "Animated infographic style video with icons and quick facts; clean, modern, British design aesthetic."}], "weekly_plan": [{"week": "Week 1", "focus": "Highlight leak-free benefits and seamless design", "publishing_goal": "Build awareness of leak prevention with seamless aluminium guttering"}, {"week": "Week 2", "focus": "Showcase maintenance-free advantages and leaf grid feature", "publishing_goal": "Educate on hassle-free upkeep and leaf protection benefits"}, {"week": "Week 3", "focus": "Emphasise colour options to boost kerb appeal", "publishing_goal": "Inspire with colour matching possibilities and design enhancement"}, {"week": "Week 4", "focus": "Detail installation options and aftercare", "publishing_goal": "Build trust by explaining downpipe compatibility and warranty clarity"}], "campaign_theme": "Seamless Aluminium Guttering for Durable, Beautiful, Low-Maintenance Homes", "content_pillars": ["Leak Prevention", "Maintenance-Free Living", "Kerb Appeal & Colour Matching", "Installation & Compatibility", "Customer Peace of Mind"], "compliance_notes": ["Ensure all claims about product lifespan and maintenance are accurate and compliant with UK advertising standards.", "Use customer testimonials with explicit permission and avoid unverifiable guarantees.", "Include appropriate disclaimers about installation variables and warranty terms.", "Avoid health and safety claims without official certification.", "Respect data privacy in all lead generation CTAs and follow GDPR regulations."]}', 0, 'social_content_pack_v1', 'gpt-4.1-mini', 'gpt-image-1', '2026-04-16 09:25:12.944+00', '2026-04-16 09:25:12.944+00');
